Title: Zone Imaging
Content:
Hi,I'm Darren. Im a photographer, husband & father (although maybe not in that order!). Im humbled that you have taken the time to view my work and learn a bit more about myself and my style of photography.

Weddings are such amazing, emotional & fun celebrations (ok, maybe a little stressful for you, but trust me everything will be ok & I will help you through it). My role is to capture all of this through my lens. I see myself as a guest at each wedding I photograph, the only difference being is that I'm a guest with a few cameras and lenses!

My way of seeing is to tell a Story of each day's events whether this is the Mehndi, Nikkah, Baraat or any other event & to give you a set of images that will show your Story unfold. I like to capture all the little details, the emotions of the day and all the traditions and customs. I am definitely not a photographer that likes to stand still. I like to listen to what you want from your wedding and then we can work together to build your pictures.

A good place to start to view my work would be on the Blog section of my site. Here you can see the Stories I have already told with a selection of images from my previous clients.

All that is left to say is to thank you for considering myself to be part of your Wedding Story. If you would like to get in contact with myself for an initial consultation please feel free to email or drop me a call.

Zeeshan Siddique Photography & Films Ltd
Content:
Our Company operated by Zeeshan Siddique ( Photographer) along with Creative Director In Cinematography Adnan khan. Both are qualified and experienced image makers.
Zeeshan Siddique is specialised in photography and have photographed many weddings all over the UK.
Adnan Khan is a qualified cinematographer and have covered number of events all over the UK.
We love what we do and it shines through our images and videos.
Our approach to Wedding Photography and Cinematography is calm and discreet, we admire being able to see the bride and groom’s faces light up when they see the photographs and video shots and say ‘I never knew you were taking those photos or video!’ we take a creative approach and seek out a mixture of candid moments, details and portraits. we make every effort to ensure your photographs and video stand out from the crowd, creating special moments of your unique day to paragon forever.
Portraits of the bride and groom are of course vital and we do our upmost to put you at comfort, so we can create beautiful photographs and video shots in various locations around your venue.
we also offer a Pre-Wedding Photo shoot, as part of the main perfect image for each and everyone of you that comes to me, whether that’s a family wanting a memorable portrait or a new model in need of fresh portfolio shots, the list is endless. We are determined to take the time to get it right for you, as each job is completely personal and tailored to achieving the best result for you.
We specialize in the following :-
Weddings
Corporate/Private Parties and Events
Fashion/Beauty
Portraiture
Commercial
we aim to satisfy all your photography and Cinematography needs and can also help with supplying models, make up artists and stylist. For more visit our galleries or Contact us.

Content:
I have been in the  wedding and portrait photography business for over 10 years now, the best thing about this business is that every day is different and every photo shoot brings something new and exciting for us all.

My career has moved direction over the years allowing me to be fortunate to adopt new and changing styles to the photogaphy scene. For me photography isnt just about taking your pictures my approach is leading the way to expressing your moments in an breath taking unique fashion.

As a freelance portrait photographer and wedding photographer I have been able to develop my film and documentary making skills into this arena giving my customers a new vision and exciting individual theme to suit their needs as well as capturing unique personality, mood and capturing moments that tell beautiful stories in years to come.

” For me, being a professional photographer has always been a dream, I am living my dream and making dreams come true for others too, i feel lucky to be apart of my other peoples happiness and capturing the magical moments in my work”.

Yours Occasionally
Content:
What makes Yours Occasionally so special? Here at Yours Occasionally I am a firm believer in delivering a highly personal service to all my clients at a competitive price, no matter how small or large their order is.

My name is Fred Foster and I founded Yours Occasionally in April 2011 when, after years of making bespoke Christmas cards to sell for charity and wedding stationery for friends, I decided I'd like to try it as a career. I am proud to say that my business has flourished, and in 2013 I won an Wedding Industry Experts Award for Best New Invitation Designer. and Best Stationer in the Essex Wedding Awards 2014. I am now working full time designing and making wedding stationery. I adore my job!

I love the personal touch and I have the ability to create completely unique designs if required, which gives my clients the satisfaction of knowing that their wedding invitations and wedding stationery are a total one off for their special day.

It's very important to me to know who my clients are, and more importantly for you to know who I am. I want to connect with you, rather than being a 'faceless' service provider.

I also want to ensure that my clients feel that they have a wonderful, high quality experience at Yours Occasionally. I understand that every wedding is unique and has a different approach which makes my work exciting and dynamic on a daily basis.

If you want to know more about Yours Occasionally, please contact me, I look forward to hearing from you!

Title: Your Wedding Shop - Wedding Dress Outlet/Wolverhampton
Your Wedding Shop - Wedding Dress Outlet
Content:
Your Wedding Shop - Wedding Dress Outlet in Birmingham, was created with a view to providing brand new, designer bridal gowns off the peg and to order, with fantastic customer service.

We have over 800 designer wedding dresses on three floors sourced direct from our wedding designer's factories and made available to you via our wedding dress outlet in Birmingham. All our designer dresses on our ground floor are here for you for ‎£495.00 or less. Although we do stock large ranges of current seasons gowns from top UK designers, also available to order or 'off the peg' for those short lead weddings, such as -: Allure Bridals, Alfred Angelo, Phil Collins Bridal, Jasmine, Jasmine Couture, Eddy K Couture, Ladybird, Sweetheart, Hermione, Maddison James. We carry amazing Plus Size ranges from -: Allure Woman, Sonsie, Alfred Angelo, Callista Plus Size, and Ladybird.

If its an Amazing 'tee length' that is your dream dress, then look no further. We guarantee that we have the largest collection of short wedding dresses in the Midlands, our collections come from Lou Lou Brides, True Brides and Louise Bentley

Our bridal dress sizes range from 6 to 30 and new stock arrives regularly, so we are confident our experienced staff will be able to assist in finding you the dress of your dreams.

Style and quality but without high prices! You can simply choose, try on, pay and then take away! No waiting for your dress to be ordered, and if your dress needs altering there is are local independent seamstresses who our brides say are fantastic, although it is important to carry out your own due diligence.

Title: 123 Photography
Content:
123Photography was established in 2002 by photographer and journalist Daniel Thubron. After gaining a Bachelor of Arts in Broadcast Journalism at Leeds University, Daniel worked as website editor at Radio Aire in Leeds before setting up 123Photography. The 123 philosophy is capturing natural images of subjects with a fun element – the best photographs are taken when least expected. A lot of 123’s work involves weddings, portraits, events and several months travelling abroad each year for travel images.
If you’ve searched for Wedding Photographers Leeds and found our website then you’re in the right place! We were recently shortlisted for NORTH EAST WEDDING PHOTOGRAPHER OF THE YEAR in the Wedding Industry Awards.
We’ve also worked for EMAP who own brands such as FHM Magazine, Heat, Smash Hits and KISS.

Content:
The Yorkshire Bridal Shop is a Mother and Daughter run affordable bridal shop in Morley, Leeds.

Hope to meet you soon!

Title: 31oh3 Photography
Content:
Hi, I am Jen and I'm a freelance female photographer based in Huddersfield, West Yorkshire, but often travel all over the UK and abroad for work, I adore destination weddings and food, eating and photographing!

Everyone seems to ask me "What does 31oh3 mean?" - it's actually my birthday (31st March)

As well as being a photographer am also a qualified and insured makeup artist, and use this for portraits, makeovers and boudoir photography. I do my own styling and have a vast array or props to suit any style of photography.

Title: 3 The Orchard, Belper, DE56 1DF
Content:
Welcome to Emily Jane Bridalwear, I specialise in bespoke, individually created,
made to measure Wedding Dresses and Special Occasion Wear,
for ladies of all ages and sizes.

Having your wedding dress made to measure is an exciting experience. If you have a design in mind, or you need some guidance, ideas or inspiration, I can help you turn your dream dress into reality.
Your dress is designed to incorporate your ideas and requirements,
and is tailor-made to your measurements, ensuring a perfect fit.

I am a professional bridal dressmaker offering a bespoke made to measure service for all the bridal party.
I hold City & Guilds qualifications and have over 20 years experience. I take immense pride in my work;
each gown is individually made by myself to the highest standards,
with great care and attention to detail.

I offer a friendly personal service, working on a one to one basis with you,
to ensure you have the perfect dress for your special day.

Beautiful Bespoke Wedding Gowns & Occasion Wear

The first step is to have a relaxed informal appointment at my studio, to discuss your ideas and wishes. You may have collected cuttings, photographs, pictures etc... showing design features that you like, if so bring them along.

You can view and try samples of my work, and look through the extensive range of beautiful bridal fabrics that are available including: Silks, Satins, Organza, Taffeta, Lace, Georgette, Chiffon, Tulle etc....
(embroidered, beaded or plain). A selection of excellent quality manmade fabrics is also available.

Having your wedding dress made especially for you isn't as expensive as you might imagine.
My prices are very competitive, and compare very favourably with ready made 'off the peg' dresses
and payment can be made in instalments at no extra cost.

Title: You Beauty Clinic
Content:
All appointments are subject to a cancellation period of a minimum of 24 hours. If cancelled within 24 hours of appointment time your booking will be subject to a cancellation fee of 50%.

For treatments over £40 a 50% deposit will be taken at time of booking.

We are located in Stone Mill, (in between Asda and The Shires).

Parking is available in the Asda and Shires car park for only 30p an hour. Once in the car park, head to The Shires entrance via the under cover walk way. The ramp will drop down to the right. Cross the link bridge into Stone Mill.

Title: 20:20 Photography
Content:
20:20 Photography is a partnership between professional photographers James Wiltshire and Nick Brenton.

James is an award winning landscape photographer based in Wiltshire and has travelled the country in search of the perfect image, waking at 3am to climb mountains in order to get the desired results. James has an outstanding eye for photographs and will go to the ends of the earth to get that perfect shot. Braving the elements regularly James is used to shooting in any situation. James resides near Salisbury, Wiltshire with his Wife and Two Sons.

Nick has been a photographer for the last 10 years. Starting his career as an assistant wedding photographer Nick has gone on to photograph fashion models for clothing companies as well as national sporting events in front of 25'000 people. He has had his work published numerous times. Nick is used to the fast paced world of photography and you need not worry about him missing a fleeting moment. Nick resides near Bath, Somerset with his Wife, Son and Daughter.

Title: Yoko's Fashion
Content:
UK's top quality costume jewellery, fashion 5e4401d23d861, handbags and scarves

Yoko's Fashion is a UK leading wholesaler offering a wide range of costume jewellery, fashion 5e4401d23d861, handbags and scarves distributor in the North West of England established in 2007. Our original wholesale warehouse was established nearly a decade ago and based in the Greater Manchester, England.

Our main objective is perfecting, importing and exporting fashion 5e4401d23d861 to the trade. We strongly believe in long lasting relationships with our customers through supplying good quality costume jewellery and other 5e4401d23d861 at reasonable prices and providing an excellent level of customer service.

We aim to provide a high quality, extensive and diverse range of products as we have a strong emphasis on customer satisfaction at all time. Therefore we will always endeavour to ensure our customer receive the best quality of products, innovation and lowest possible price. We pride ourselves on working professionally and taking the utmost care to respect our customers requirements at all times.

We exhibit at various major tradeshows throughout the year including NEC ‘Spring Fair’ in February and ‘Autumn Fair’ in September. We provide a wide range of costume jewellery on display, which is an ideal opportunity for us to guide you as to our popular and bestsellers collection of jewellery.

Additionally, in recent years, we operated a wholesale website for our trader. As an alternatively, customers are welcome to place an order on our wholesale website at any time. The company's competitiveness is due to a continual in-depth analysis of the markets and of the existing and potential requirements, associated with a willingness to innovate new production lines. Therefore we continuous to innovate and implement new production lines at all time to invest the most advanced costume jewellery in the market and increase service efficiency. Consequently, continuous improvement and complete customer satisfaction is the heart of Yoko's Fashion.

Title: Yewbank Catering
Content:
Yewbank Catering provide quality catering for all occasions. We have successfully traded for 15 years and we have a lot of happy customers who use our services again and again. Most of our food is home made on our premises using only the finest suppliers and quality ingredients.

We provide a selection of menus to suit any occasion and will give you help and advice while you choose, we welcome any suggestions and amendments to the menus to suit your likes and needs. The menus range from casual buffets to carving buffets to sit down meals, and the service from discreet delivery to formal ‘black and white’ waitress service.

If you are working to a budget please do not hesitate to contact us as prices vary and we can discuss your options personally. We also offer a discount to larger numbers of over 100 guests. We offer a unique, friendly and professional catering service throughout West Yorkshire and the Yorkshire dales, so give us a call for your special day and let us put you at ease and take care of all your catering needs.

We offer full catering services for all occasions in West Yorkshire, North Yorkshire and Lancashire within a fifty mile radius of Ilkley. However, we will consider other areas.

Title: Yellow12 Photography
Content:
I love to create beautiful images that tell the story of a wedding day. The pictures I take are honest whilst being creative. Sometimes they are whimsical or quirky, sometimes they will be serious. Above all, I strive to take pictures which will be timeless. No gimmicks, no fuss.

I shoot portraits from time to time too. I bring the same ethos to these as I do with my wedding photography.

If you like the way I capture images, I'd love to hear from you.

Title: Yellow Door
Content:
The Yellow Door began life as a fine dining restaurant in Gilford, Co.Down in 1992. Due to demand for a more informal food offering the Yellow Door Deli opened in Portadown in 1997. The restaurant was later sold and the deli and bakery business expanded, giving rise to other delis and a busy outside catering business.

We have a great team, and lots of family! Simon Dougan runs the deli in Portadown, the outside catering business, and the newest addition to the family, Native by Yellow Door at the MAC. Andrew (his cousin) opened the delis in Belfast and Lisburn and runs the catering at the Ulster Museum and for Ulster Rugby. Gary (Andrew’s brother) runs the wholesale side of the business supplying discerning restaurants all over Ireland with daily deliveries of fresh bread and patisserie. Jilly (Simon’s wife) manages the Yellow Door kitchen garden and other growing projects at our outlets.

There are a plethora of other Dougans working in the Yellow Door, everywhere from the accounts department to the kitchens and the pastry section.

It gets a bit manic at times but the one thing that unites everyone is a passion for fabulous, locally produced food, and a desire to get the very best out of it.

Title: 2 Ice 2 Eat
Content:
Are you planning a birthday?

Title: YCM Weddings & Events
Content: Founded by Louise and Craig, YCM Weddings and Events is a unique, bold and creative, wedding and event planning and styling company based in Crewe, Cheshire. With a great Passion for the wedding and event industry YCM offer everything from a full planning service to on the day coordination so there really is something to suit each individual couples style and need. Events are a big part of what we do, and we love to plan them! We have provided our services for a range of events including charity parties, conferences and wedding fayres both independently and for 5e44098b859ec. We have big plans for the future and lots more events that we have in the pipeline to host. We cover Crewe, Nantwich, Sandbach, Middlewich, Winsford, Shavington, Wrenbury, Wychwood village, the whole of Cheshire and surrounding areas. Please take a look through our services and get in touch for a no-obligation consultation.

Title: Yavani
Content:
Here at Yavani we have spent over a decade searching the globe for the best fabrics and costume jewellery. With our sharp eye for design and fashion we can one of the largest selections of costume jewellery and asain bridal wear in the country.

All our garments can be made to measure and in a base tone colour of your choice.

Have a look at the products on our site and if you like something, buy it now online and either have it posted out the next day or come over to the shop the same day to collect.

Feel free to come to the store to see our selection, we can better advise in store other variations and styles available.

All colours available in net fabric. Not all colours are available on raw and pure silk.

All seasonal colours are available in raw and pure silk. Should you have a request for an unusual colour, these swatches can be ordered on request.

For all made to measure outfits, we take measurements in store based on appointment.

We can work to provided measurements but strongly recommend you allow us to ensure they are correct. If you chose not to we take not responsibility should these measurements be incorrect when fitted.

We gaurantee the outfits will be to the exact dimensions provided. Again we prefer to take the measurements ourselves as we have many years of experience and continue to delight our clients with the final result.

We also offer made to measure blouses to your specific style requirements.

All lengha blouses and dpatti can be made into sarees. All colour available on Georgette.

All outfits should only be cleaned by specialist dry cleaners. Never put in the washing machine!

Title: Yasin Catering Ltd
Content:
As a family run business, we understand how important special occasions such as weddings, engagements and birthdays are to you and your guests.

Our highly experienced chefs and caterers will prepare delicious, authentic Asian food that everyone can enjoy, ensuring that your event is stress free and enjoyable for all. With a wide choice of expertly prepared halal meat and vegetarian dishes, you can tailor your menu to suit your personal tastes and preferences.

If you need a venue to host your banquet, we are proud to announce our partnership with White Rose Banqueting. Perfect for wedding feasts, business conferences, charity fundraisers or any other occasion, we work alongside them to ensure that your event goes smoothly from start to finish.

We also believe in giving back to the community, which is why we cater for charity events and food handouts throughout Leeds each year.

Title: XXI Hair Design
Content:
Our hair salon offers all customers a varied base of experience for all aspects of hairdressing, including senior stylists and an artistic director.

-
Students receive 15% off all hair treatments from Monday to Friday.

Each customer receives a free consultation and a complimentary tea or Cooper's coffee.

Title: X-Perience Boudoir Photography
Content:
The build up to the boudoir shoot is seen as very much as part of the experience. First choosing your lingerie is seen as a sumptuous affair and treasured by women. After all, this is not about comfort and practicality: this lingerie is actually going to be seen, albeit by invitation!
On the day itself, the shoot can start with a glass of bubbly followed by our in house professional make up artist applying your make up as desired charged at £30. This all helps to relax and place the woman in the right positive frame of mind.
The photography itself is a continuation of the pampering theme. Sessions are carried out by a female photographer even printed & framed by myself. The best boudoir photographers are skilled in putting the woman at ease and bringing out the best in them, I use a subtle caress of light to create a intimate atmosphere-and careful posing to bring out the woman's individuality.
The more relaxed and trusting the subject is, the better the results. Results that will last a LIFETIME.

Title: X S Hair Ltd
Content:
Voted best hair & beauty salon in Leeds, this elite hair team are offering fantastic hair and beauty services at competitive prices. Owner Sara Turner is an expert in hairdressing along with her team of hand picked, elite stylists and colourists form a formidable and passionate Leeds city center salon, styling Leeds for over 17 years. Education and passion are our driving force, together with creating a relaxing, fun and friendly environment to ensure the very best in customer care.

NEW! Home of one of the first cosmetic Cryotherapy treatment machines in the UK, XS is at the forefront of the hair and beauty industry.

What is Cryotherapy? Cryotherapy treatments originated in Japan in the early 1970’s and are currently in use worldwide. The liquid nitrogen based freezing technology uses vapours reaching below -160°C, in order to trigger a physiological reaction to cold temperatures. The brain then receives messages to stimulate the regulatory functions of the body. This extreme cold causes the body to increase its metabolic rate in order to produce heat, meaning that the body burns between 500-800 calories in the hours following the procedure.

Title: Wye Valley Studios
Content:
We offer a high quality framing service for photographs, paintings, artwork, memorabilia, tapestries etc. and carry a large selection of mouldings in our well equipped framing department. We can cut bevel mounts and multi mounts and are able to print your own photos from your memory cards, memory sticks, or CD/DVD. These can be printed on professional inkjet paper with canvas printing also available. Sizes upto 40 x 30 inches are possible as long as your file size is large enough. We can also copy and enlarge your old photos with our Copycraft service.

Ready made frames in standard sizes are available in our retail area and we can make frames to your requirements from a varied selection of modern and traditional styles.

Framed photographs of local views are on display for sale in our gallery by award winning landscape photographer Nick House and he is also available for commissions if you have a favourite place you would like photographed.

Title: Written with Light Photography
Content:
Before my love of photography began, there were stories...and I cannot remember a time when I wasn't preoccupied with books; adventurers, chivalrous heroes and beautiful heroines all captured my imagination invoking thousands of images. It was an obvious choice therefore for me to pursue a degree in English Literature, allowing me three years to submerse myself in words, ideas and stories. My love of photography was slow growing, and somewhat taken for granted until it was deep-rooted. I’m not at all unique in saying that some of my most treasured possessions in life are photographs. Most people would say that in a burning building situation - the one thing they would want to rescue (usually after family members!) is a photograph or a photo album.

The age we live in is fast paced, vibrant and multi-sensory, we are bombarded with images minute by minute and yet a simple photograph still has the power to capture our imaginations and to stop us in our tracks with the remembrance of a single moment. At the age of 12, I was given my first film camera as a birthday present, and after my Dad had shown me how to load the film I abandoned the celebrations to arrange and photograph my presents, I snapped my birthday cake before it was demolished and took candid shots of my friends and family, haphazardly trying to cram into the frame all the important details that I desperately wanted to record. Waiting for the film to be developed was always the painful part and the anticipation of collecting my prints was such that I would not be able to resist a furtive peak through the collection on my way out of the shop. I would pore over the pictures again and again, usually despairing over the lack of light or blurriness of the shot, nevertheless they were my treasures. Over time this excitement has increased and thanks to digital photography my pictures improved! I have spent increasingly more and more time taking photographs and developing my knowledge; this will be a lifelong process that I happily undertake.

It was a natural progression in some ways linking my love of stories and romance with my love of wedding photography. I am, I suppose, a hopeless romantic and therefore everything about weddings appeals to me. In the same way that I felt a burning need to capture every part of my birthday on film, I am overtaken at weddings with the need to record. I believe it is true that “the camera has power beyond the photographer to record the emotion that only the heart can see”(Joan Bauer) and it is this power that captivates myself as the photographer and us all as viewers. There is no greater privilege than being allowed to document the life stories of others, my camera provides a doorway to your world and through it I view your most precious moments and in turn freeze those moments for you to enjoy and wonder at in years to come.

Thank you for viewing my images and taking the time to look at my site, maybe our stories will merge at some point… I look forward to that possibility!

Hannah

Title: A Bride-2-Bee
Content:
We began 15 years ago when we realised there was a need for spacious, fun, friendly bridal and occasion wear stores that welcomed customers with a smile and treated them like a VIP. We also wanted to bring great quality style from incredible designers to our customers.

Our philosophy was simple, to make the experience of choosing a dress as special as the day itself, adding to the whole wedding experience, creating a buzz of excitement leading up to the big day.

From brides who envisaged their big day from a young age, to those who want to get married within weeks we ensure the entire journey, no matter how long or short is stress free.

We’re proud that we’ve gained an exceptional reputation for doing just that (just take a look at our testimonials page) while elite designers have chosen us to display and retail their fabulous dresses to you.

Over the years our range of designers has grown considerably and we’ve become immersed in the world of weddings. All of us genuinely care about each and every customer that crosses our threshold and we feel privileged to be part of making their day extra special.

We have also ensured we offer the perfect place for trying on that perfect dress with an aisle that allows you to see what the groom will see as you walk towards that loving smile. Our customer service and extensive range has been so popular that we’ve listened to feedback expanded our range of bridesmaid, special occasion wear and prom dresses into our lines.

Now we offer extras that promise to make the lead up to any life changing event fun and full of happiness, while constantly adding to our collections so we can offer gorgeous dresses to suit any special occasion, figure, style or budget.

Our team can’t wait to meet you, get a heads up and learn more about them here. You can also find out more about our exclusive designers that turn your wedding into the event of the year!

We recycle our Printer Cartridges

Title: A Big Day
Content:
Everyone Is Welcome

Greetings from the team. Vicky and the girls at "A Big Day” have been helping brides find the perfect dresses for over 10 years. We have created a relaxed and friendly atmosphere where you can get everything for your big day from shoes & 5e4401d23d861 to lingerie & night wear.
Aberdeen bridal wear

The North East's Leading Bridal Wear Company, Bring You "A BIG DAY".
To help you have the best experience you can when preparing for your big day, at A Big Day we offer an experienced and friendly service to brides in the Grampian area and beyond.

Title: A Place for Beauty
Content: A Place for Beauty offers a professional personal service in beauty therapy, make up services for brides, bridal party and for all other occasions. The products used, such as OPI and Liz Earle, are of high prestigeous quality, offering a luxurious and personalised treatment. The therapist offers skin care advice and treatments, waxing service, manicures, pedicures, eyelash treatments and Semi Permanent Makeup (SPMU).

Title: A Perfect Memory
Content:
Welcome to A Perfect Memory

We would like to thank you for your interest in A Perfect Memory and hope your wedding day is perfect in every way possible.

We use the latest in HD video technology to capture every precious moment of your wedding day. Then each DVD is lovingly edited to bring the whole event to life and give each couple a stunning record of the day to enjoy for years to come.

Title: Witney Weddings Photography
Content:
Witney Weddings Photography is Jakob Tungelund & Pawel Sytniewski. Pawel and Jakob have been both educated to HNC level in Photography in Oxford and are members of the Society of Wedding and Portrait Photographers (SWPP). They are also listed with the Trusted Photographer program and have full photographic insurance.

Jakob's approach is fly-on-the-wall style documentary, preferring mainly to shoot unposed candid portraits and capturing each special moment as it passes. Jakob likes to encapsulate people's emotions and the overall feel of the couple's special day within his work.

Pawel's photography is always concentrated on the feelings and emotions that are constantly transferred between people. "Every change in a relation reveals in a photo. Being discrete and unnoticed is as important as being a part of the company" says Pawel and this is a key part of the way both Pawel & Jakob work.

They both strive to work together and apart; to create a dynamic story of precious memories seen and those moments which were swept away unnoticed which you can look back upon and treasure for the rest of your lives.

Title: A Page Photography
Content:
Picking a wedding photographer is an important decision for your big day so it is important that you feel comfortable with whoever you choose. Over the last 15 years I have tailored my wedding photography packages to suit you, the bride and groom, however, every couple is different so I always like to meet you both in person a couple of times prior to your wedding, so you can get to know me, and I can find out more about your plans and understand the kinds of images you’ll want.
I am a female Nuneaton wedding photographer covering Warwickshire, West Midlands and Leicestershire.

I now also offer an Engagement Photography package which is a great way for us to get to know each other and work out what you want from your wedding photography.

Please browse through my gallery and if you have any questions or would like to know more then please contact me on 07739 546809 or email me directly.

Title: A Little Bit of Blighty Ltd

He provides an end to end service from image capture to re-touched photographs, through to end user marketing materials with a clean and thoughtful style. Focused on automotive and product photography for private, editorial and business clients.

Title: Wiltshire Flowers
Content: Welcome to Wiltshire Flowers, an independent and small business florist in Wiltshire,  based in the market town of Melksham.  I'm Jo Brookes and apart from living and working in Germany and the USA for 10 years,  Wiltshire has always been my home county.    It has been a fulfilling journey from once having a hobby and passion for flowers into becoming a qualified florist and running my own business. I truly believe in celebrating 'small' because as a small business I have the flexibility to add a personal unique touch to every order that leaves the premises.  It's more than just supplying a product and as such I have a loyal customer base who place their flower orders with me time and time again. It goes without saying that as a wedding specialist that personal service goes a long way with our wedding couples from the moment of consultation to the day of the wedding itself.

Title: WILLOWSTONE PHOTOGRAPHY
Content:
Here at Snap in a Box photobooth hire we pride ourselves on our commitment to go that extra mile to make your event both unique and special, with our dedicated team of friendly trained operators and our ultimate customer care for every occasion.

Whether you are planning a Wedding, Birthday celebration or any event, a “Snap in a Box” photobooth is guaranteed to be a hit and keep everyone talking about it long after the event! When you hire a “Snap in a Box” Photobooth all of our packages include unlimited prints so there is no cap on the amount of photos that can be taken on the night.

Additional prints of the same photo can be ordered on the night as our software allows us to be very versatile. Our booths can be customised with your unique graphics to either promote your event or even personalise your booth at your party. All our photo booths use only the highest quality cameras and printers, no matter what booth you book you will receive outstanding photos.

We use dye-sub printers which print out images almost instantly and guarantee the best quality photos in the industry. We can supply your photos in many different formats and customised with your logo or personalised message. We can also supply a guest book, and a double set of prints. Have a look over our FAQ Page for more information.

Title: William Platt Photography
Content:
In essence, I am a down to earth family man, who loves photography with a passion and my work is a personal reflection of my own exacting standards and close attention to detail.
But when I’m not behind a camera, I like to run and keep fit – and love taking long rides out on my Motorbike. I am always around at the Isle Of Man T.T. Races come June with my camera ready, hoping for that one in a million shot, and have previously covered the event for the Sport sections of my local and also regional media publishers.
Working around the North west has been my life and I like to give a little in return for all the support that my local community have given me over the years. So I give up some of my free time covering local Charity Events, ie. Salford School events, the G festival , fun runs and many more.

Title: Why Eye Photography Ltd
Content:
Stuart Forster is a professional photographer and features writer.

Stuart is shortlisted for the National Geographic Traveller Photographer of the Year Award (2013). He was shortlisted for the German Travel Writer of the Year Award (2010) and nominated in the Travel Photojournalism category of the Pacific Asia Travel Association (PATA) Gold Awards (2007). One of his images was selected for the National Union of Journalists' 2009 Photography Matters exhibition, showing leading news photos from 2007 and 2008.

His work has been published in magazines, newspapers and books around the world. These include newspapers such as theWashington Post, Guardian, Financial Times, Independent, The Age and Sydney Morning Herald plus magazines such asIrish Tatler Man, The Wisden Cricketer, Real Travel Magazine and Tatler. He also contributed to the National Geographic book,Secret Journeys of a Lifetime (2011).

Stuart has lived in India and explored Kerala while researching Driving Holidays Across India (Outlook Traveller, 2009) and wrote about snakeboat racing in guidebook Kerala(Stark World, 2006). He travelled extensively in Karnataka while researching Bengaluru and Karnataka (Stark World, 2008); his experiences ranged from drinking tea with a maharaja to trekking in the jungle. It meant eating food from streetside handcarts and in five star restaurants.

His photos have appeared numerous books, including The Wisden Cricketer's Almanack(Wisden, 2009), China - Eine Bildreise andIndien - Eine Bildreise (National Geographic, 2008), Dresden (Bradt Guides, 2007), The Seventy Wonders of China (Thames & Hudson, 2007) and Uebelsetzungen(Langenscheidt, 2007).

Stuart believes photographic images are more than just documentary; they can inform and lead to greater understanding of the world. Photographs can bring people to question what is happening around them and in distant lands, engendering interest in places, people and cultures.

Stuart frequently travels to research stories, aiming to capture the spirit of places and events. His passions include trying local cuisine, exploring history as well as experiencing the culture and contemporary attractions of destinations.

His images have been exhibited at China's Pingyao International Photography Festival (2006) and at London's Zimbabwe House (2010).

PDFs of his published work can be sent on request. Feel free to make contact and to commission work.

Title: A Little Bit of Blighty Ltd
Content:
A Little Bit of Blighty Ltd is a charismatic shop in Cannock, Staffordshire. Come and visit us and see what little Vintage surprises we may have for you to reminisce of 'days gone by'. Maybe you would just like to browse through our vintage style gifts and treat a friend or even better treat yourself......

Or perhaps you are planning a party or wedding and would like to take advantage of our event planning service. We pride ourselves in creating a unique day no matter how big or small your day maybe.

Title: A J Images
Content:
Dedicated to providing a quality and professional service

A J Images is a Cambridge based company specialising in photographic work and can cater for all of your requirements. With over 20 years of experience in photography, the owner set up A J Images in 2001 to meet the demands of an ever changing world and market place.

Whatever the photography service that you require, A J Images will offer you a professional and personal service, tailoring each project to meet your specific needs.

We can supply photographic material in any desired format; colour or black & white prints and transparencies produced from professional film or digital files supplied onto a CD.

Supporting the third world

As an established supplier of worldwide travel photography along with illustrating the plight of the third world and the ever-changing environment, A J Images has also introduced a new and exciting range of products.

We offer an outstanding selection of stunning original art from South East Asia, which A J Images is proud to state is purchased directly from local artists in an effort to stimulate their local economy and to help fight disease, famine along with enabling their children to be educated.

The proprietor of A J Images has been involved in many local projects over the past few years:

Helping village schools in Laos with supplies, documenting the plight of indigenous tribes in Burma, working with land-mine disposal organisations in Cambodia & Laos, setting up trade for local suppliers directly to the UK from Vietnam, help protect elephants in Northern Thailand and many other small projects in Laos, Cambodia, Indonesia, Borneo, Thailand & Vietnam.

We offer a professional and personal catering service for all types of events. We tailor-make our menus to suit individual requirements.

Title: A Great Pose Ltd
Content:
Hello thank you for taking the time to visit our web site.

Please feel free to look at all of our pages and you will start to get a good idea of the type of photography work we do. At A Great Pose Ltd our aim is to create fantastic photographs of your special day, whatever the occasion, and provide you with images that will help you remember those great moments forever.

Whether it is a wedding, civil partnership,family portrait, birthday party, pregnancy bump or other celebration we have the flair and skills to produce photographs you will be proud to show off to family and friends. We can even cover proms, balls and other events which may require us to print there and then to give straight to the customer.

We are a very friendly Husband and Wife team who work hard to make sure we get you exactly what you wanted.

Photos are important to us and we know they are to you too so have a look at what we do and feel free to contact us for a chat.

Here's what someone had to say about a recent shoot,

My daughter was a bridesmaid at the wedding of Nick and Dani. We have just looked through their gallery and wow the photos are great. Just trying to choose what to order! Very artistic! What a lovely day.

Thanks again and we hope to speak with you soon.

Title: WHITE DOVE PHOTOGRAPHY
Content:
For those who choose me to be their wedding photographer I always make sure I take the time to get to know them.

Understanding what they want to achieve from their wedding or photo shoot is essential because, to me, that understanding is key to delivering beautiful photographs which people will be proud of now and for years to come.

My style of photography incorporates classic, contemporary, fun and modern styles that I hope you find honest, beautiful and emotive. This stems from my passion for photography and I aim to exceed all of my client’s expectations.

Photography has always been a part of my life whether it was capturing a golden beach sunset, fast jets or a cheeky smile from my children. Commercial clients include NHS, RAF Air Cadets and Synergy Events Emerging Trends Fashion Show in Paris.

Although we do work internationally we are based in Clevedon, North Somerset and work mainly in The Cotswolds, Avon, Bristol, Merseyside, Liverpool, Portishead, The South West, Somerset, Devon & Cornwall.
My other passion is flying and aviation and if I am not behind the lens then I am often found behind the controls of one aircraft or

Title: White Cloud Photographic

Title: White Balloon Films
Content:
White Balloon Films Wedding Videography: Part 1 – Alina
Well, what can I say about my beautiful wife (she’s the one in the left of the above photo)…

Alina is the creative genius behind White Balloon Films. A graduate of film and animation from the London College of Communication, I am blessed to not only be married to this wonderful person but to be in business with her too. Alina is not only educated in film and animation but prior to the creation of White Balloon Films in 2012, worked at several of London’s premier production companies before moving to Glasgow and establishing her own company specialising in stop-motion animations for corporate clients. It is this foundation of technique and talent that underpins our approach at White Balloon Films and makes us quite unique.

White Balloon Films Wedding Videography: Part 2 – Stewart
After those kind words Stewart I feel under pressure to complement you too…!

How can I say this nicely…Stewart was a banker before he met me. Okay, well that’s not entirely true, “portfolio manager in London for one of the world’s leading hedge funds” as he likes to put it but “banker” rolls off the tongue a little easier! A few years on, Stewart is my extremely talented fellow camera operator and editor. As my husband, we work in a synchronised and coordinated way when filming, massively increasing the quality of our footage. It is a fantastic partnership characterised by my ‘creativity’ combined with his relentlessly analytical approach to filming.

Title: Whisk
Content:
Whisk Home Baked Cakes in Glasgow
Whisk has grown from making friends and family smile to giving guests something to marvel at. Even with its wide range of clients, Whisk food never loses its hand made character and taste. The quality and nostalgia that Whisk evokes through home cooking are its cornerstone. Whether it be a tray of canapés to impress new clients, a celebration cake with home baked flavour or a wedding cake to remember, Whisk food is a delicious experience that our clients come back to time and again.

Title: Whelan Photography
Content:
We are Shane and Claire and we have been married for5 years. We are friendly and fun and we like to think that that is reflected in our photography. Being around friends and family is great so weddings are a brilliant way of being able to photograph real emotion and we really love capturing these amazing moments. Our style is very unobtrusive so we won’t take over your day; instead, we will disappear into the background and capture natural, beautiful photographs. Our work is contemporary, but we deliver pictures that will be beautiful now and for many years to come. The added benefit of having two photographers is there is twice as much opportunity to capture those magical moments. We feel that photographing one of the most important days in a couples life is a real privilege so we know how important great service is.

In our lives, our families are very important so we love documenting them in photographs. We love gorgeous little new born babies to grandparents who love their families unconditionally. We provide pictures that make you relive that experience when you look back on them. We like portraits to be fun and natural so a walk in the park or relaxing in your garden is ideal!

When we aren't taking pictures Shane will usually be playing guitar and making a racket while I will be crafting on the sofa or baking. We really enjoy days out at the beach, historical cities (more Shane than me, I just like shopping!) and lazy days in watching a box set! To see our latest work have a look on our blog! We hope you enjoy looking around our website and if you have any questions please get in touch! We would love to hear from you!

Title: Wheels of Joy Photography
Content:
’m Marie Gardiner, a professional photographer specialising in weddings and commercial photography.  I’m based in Sunderland but cover the whole of the North East. I also write learning aids for aspiring photographers for a website called Tuts+.

The important thing for me about taking photographs for people is the relationship you build and maintain.  Being a photographer is a very personal thing, so it’s important you like me as well as trust me to deliver the very best photographs for you.

I love coffee a tiny bit more than any sane person should, so I’m always happy  to meet up over a cup to chat through any questions you might have.

Title: What a Picture Photography Ltd
Content:
What a Picture Photography is a family run business which mainly serves the Midlands and surrounding areas. Travelling to other areas is easily arranged. The team comprises Andrew and Kevin who have been photographers for more years than either care to remember and Kathleen who is our secretary and assists us on shoots with everything from holding lights to baby minding for a spell. We mainly photograph weddings which are our favourite type of work. Each one is different even if it’s at a location that we have worked at before. Our favourite type of venue are old churches with some history behind them as it provides a feel for the occasion rather than a location which could be transplanted anywhere. 5e44098b859ec with big gardens are also a favourite.

Don’t forget if you’re a guest at a wedding that we are photographing that it’s an ideal chance to get a portrait taken in your outfit. Very few people take up the offer, make use of us whilst we’re there is my advice, particularly if you have your young children with you.It also gives the happy couple more to choose from for their wedding album.

Title: West Yorkshire Wedding Photographer
Content:
Rick and Dena were married on Saturday at Brayton church on the outskirts of Selby before celebrating at The Pavilion Hotel in York. Our day began with Dena’s bridal preparation at their home before we joined Rick and the grooms men at church for some photographs pre-wedding ceremony.  The vicar had a great and relaxed attitude to photography in Church and so we were able to maximise the photo opportunities with myself at the front and Sophie the second photographer shooting from the back. The weather forecast had predicted showers rolling in from lunchtime and so as Rick and Dena left church we were conscious of the need to maximise any dry spell and quickly complete any formal group requests at the church. Thankfully the weather held throughout the journey to The Pavilion Hotel in York and all the way through the drinks reception only actually raining after the guests had taken their seats for the wedding breakfast.

During the pre-wedding shoot and meeting with Rick and Dena we’d discussed the proximity of York Minster and the fact that it was here that Rick proposed made a visit a high priority. Late evening we quickly sneaked away for a trip into the city centre and made  a visit to York Minster not far from the actual spot of the proposal. We then headed into Shambles, one of the most historic streets in York and one high on any tourist list of sights and places to see in the city for the final end of night photographs. The final photograph (above) will make a stunning double page spread in an Italian Storybook.

Title: West Yorkshire Photography
Content:
Photography is an important aspect of any event, all of our photographs are taken with you in mind assisting you in creating the perfect images, capturing the happiest most memorable moments and helping you keep them forever.

 WY Photography consists of 2 wedding photographers from Huddersfield situated in the heart of west Yorkshire.  We provide services ranging from Weddings, family portraits, fun photo booth shoots, event coverage and even babies first photos. You will find explanations of what we have to offer in each section but if you need any further information regarding any of our services please do not hesitate to contact us via email, phone or our contact page.

We hope you enjoy looking through our website and we hope to you hear from you soon.

Title: West Midlands
Content:
I will always remember when my Mother retired from British Rail, and they had a retirement party for her along with a few other retiring at the same time from Wolverhampton.

My mother brought me a very basic camera that did the job, and ever since that tender age of 16 years of age my interest in photography was born until today.

Some of my highlights that I have really enjoyed, was being part of the 2006 Brit Awards Event Team and more recently being responsible for the Birth of The Image Makers Network, who were the Official Photographers to document the journey of the Jamaican and USA Track and Field Team including Jamaica 50th Celebration for Birmingham City Council Legacy Project 2012.

As a Location Photographers, we are available for Weddings and most Events Photograph assignments, which again has allowed me and my team to work for some interesting Families/Couples including many Charity Organisations, along with the Police and Local Authorities and many Corporate Organisations and Community Organisations.

Once I have that camera in my hand and I have captured A Moment In Time, I just love to see the expression on my clients faces of the work I have produced.

Images that In many cases will be part of many family and organisation legacy, with my name firmly associated with their story of event.

Image with Usain Bolt and my partner Angela was taken by Mr Rod Leon from London at the University of Birmingham Welcome Dinner to the City of Birmingham a few weeks before the 2012 Olympics.

Title: West Bar Photography
Content:
West Bar Photography specialise in Wedding, Portrait, Event and Commercial Photography.

Our Wedding Photography is based around your wishes and requirements and covers the whole event from bride preparations to the last dance, with high quality photos available for anyone to view or purchase on the day.

Our style of photography is to capture your special day in a professional and relaxed manner making sure that everyone enjoys the wedding day. A full range of photos are taken in both a formal and reportage style.

The current fee for all day and evening coverage is £700 (£150 deposit secures the day) with the balance of £550 payable one month prior to your wedding day. Payments can be made by instalments to spread the cost if you so wish. Please contact us anytime to discuss further or to arrange a no obligation visit.

Event Photography - Have your event photographed with instant prints available for guests to purchase at the event or hire us on a pre-paid basis inclusive of prints for your event with full size photos taken both indoors or outdoors. A props box is also available along with green screen facilities to add further enjoyment to your wedding or event.

Title: West 70 Photography
Content:
West 70 Photography is a company founded by Adam and Marcus from Jonesco Media. Internationally award-winning experts of the wedding and media industry. Their founding idea was simple: offer photography without fuss but not compromising on quality or service. This first started with just wedding photography in 2009 but soon branched out into studio and event photography as well.

We are independently owned and believe in giving our customers more than any of our professional competitors. We also believe in transparency – this means clear pricing that’s easy to understand without any catches. Further to this we do not have any sales targets or use pushy tactics to pressure our customers into services they do not want. We make everything clear and price everything simply so that our customers can pick what they want without any misdirection.

The team of West 70 Photographers are all very skilled and have been carefully selected due to both their skill and personality. All of our team have a wonderful creative eye and capture images in a stylish yet simplistic way. Another key factor we believe in is organisation, meaning we can make the most of the time spent photographing. We are making the wedding photography, studio photography and event photography process simple and stress-free for you, our customer.

You don’t have to pay a fortune for all of this. Our wedding pricing and studio photography pricing is so affordable because you only have to pay for what you want and nothing more. We also have a skilled team of photographers meaning we can assign more than one photographer on a date, this is another way we can pass on savings to you. We are very clear about what you get for your money, so you know exactly what you are paying for and how much it’ll cost.

We also believe in your images being just that – yours. We provide a copyright permission notice with all of our work so that you can print and share your images however you want, for personal use. We don’t compress or watermark our images either, when we say they are your images we mean it!

West 70 Photography may be low cost but this doesn’t mean you have to sacrifice good customer service – far from it. Why not read what our past customers have said about our service? We offer fantastic service to you throughout the process – we want to make sure you are happy. We are a full time business, unlike many low cost photography companies, and we operate every day of the year.

No hassle. No fuss. No hidden costs. This is our very simple approach to wedding photography and studio photography and it’s proven to be very popular.

If you want to ask us anything or have an enquiry please do contact us, we would be delighted to hear from you.

Title: West 70 Photography
Content:
Welcome to West 70 Photography.

We are a professional, affordable, independently owned photography company based in Bristol, UK. We specialise in wedding photography and studio photography (at our lovely photographic studio in Downend, Bristol).

Our style is very simple and effective. Simple photography means the very best quality at an affordable price. We make sure we provide our customers with an excellent experience from start to finish. Customer satisfaction is incredibly important to us and we work hard to make sure all of our customers are happy with the service we provide. This is reflected in our customer testimonials.

We believe in natural, no-hassle photography. This means we make the most of our time with you and make sure it’s a comfortable, enjoyable environment for photographs. We like to keep things casual and light hearted all the while producing some beautiful images for you.

We don’t use pushy sales tactics and we do not have sales goals. This means you are welcome to spend as much or as little as you would like with no pressure from us. In addition to this we also make sure our pricing is clear and easy to understand with no hidden costs.

We do not impose any copyright restrictions for personal use – this means you can print and share your photographs however you like. No catches or surprises later on. We want you to enjoy your images and to share them however you like without any fuss.

Our experienced team of photographers are friendly, talented and driven to provide you with the best possible service. If you have any questions please contact us, we’re here to help however we can.

Title: Weezie Peezie
Content: SCLaser is a newly setup business which produces and sells personalised gifts and products at competitive prices. We have been running for just under a year and we are trying to expand our range of items available.  Please feel free to browse our products and thank you for taking the time to visit.  If you have see us at a recent craft fair and the items you are interested in are not available then please contact me with the details and I will get back in touch.

Title: Weddingsbygiles
Content: My name is Giles Bracher, I am an English photographer with over 25 years experience in the media industry and I specialise in shooting destination weddings. I am privileged to have had clients including, Amir Khan (Boxer), Natalie Pinkham, (Television presenter), Sam Branson (son of Sir Richard Branson) and Hello Magazine, as well as many others not in the public eye, invite me into their lives at a very intimate time and entrust me with the capturing of their precious moments all over the world. I take great pride in that trust and in their joy at receiving the unique and memorable photographs I create.

Title: Weddings by Evans
Content:
My name is Evans, a young, friendly , vibrant and artistic photographer based in the West Midlands, professionally qualified in Photography and Fine art with a BA Hons Degree. I’ve had a hard time talking about myself as I find the “about me” section quite cheesy so here’s some random facts about me.

- I’m a curious researcher , a must find the answer kind of a guy. I’ve been fortunate enough to have photographed some of the coolest and down to earth people so far in my years as a photographer. Creating beautiful photographs is something that I’ve always been deeply passionate about for years and I enjoy every single second of the process. I enjoy observing, documenting, capturing the tears, emotion, laughter, cuddles at your wedding which is the basis of my work. My clients really make me one of the happiest guy you’ll meet, It’s a great feeling when I can get to tell people, I LOVE my job, how many people can really say that ?!

- I love driving, I think i’ts one of the greatest things ever , as long as I’ve got some good music I can drive for days. And yes I live in the WestMidlands & I drive from Birmingham, Warwickshire to all the points in and around Staffordshire.

- There’s so much more , but I’m more interested in knowing about YOU ! , So lets do it over coffee , tea and biscuits, at my studio, comfort of your own home or over the phone, e-chat, you name it. Tell Me Everything ! I want to get to know you, so that I can capture your relationship and how you relate to one another. Your wedding destination , Is your wedding at a church, registration, hotel or castle ? So please feel free to contact me and I can pop out to see you .

Title: Weddings & Dreams
Content:
After the wedding ceremony your guests will spend the majority of their day sat around the table enjoying good food and conversation and, of course, the odd glass of champagne.  Weddings and dreams specialise in making that time as memorable as possible.

Weddings and Dreams co-ordinate with you and your wedding planner to provide beautiful table and chair dressings.  Choosing from a wide variety of hand picked colours and materials we carefully dress your tables and chairs creating an elegant finish to your ceremony and wedding reception.

Title: weddingphotographeryork.com
Content:
I am a skilled professional photographer with many years' experience: I will alter my style of work as you request.  I will take formal photographs, informal or quirky, different ones - the choice is up to you.  Once you have instructed me how you want your pictures to look and briefed me on as many of the groups as possible, you will just be able to relax and enjoy your day.

Pamela is a very experienced photographer with a natural ability to capture all the special moments which make your wedding day unique.  Both of us will attend your wedding to provide far greater coverage than one photographer working alone could hope for.

Title: Weddingjem
Content:
Designing and making is something that Ailsa Rendell has been interested in from an early age. Ailsa trained at the Royal Scottish Academy Of Music And Drama in Glasgow where she specialised in Costume Design and Costume Making. She then worked in the world of theatre and film for a number of years before turning her hand to Bespoke Occasional wear.

Ailsa's career has taken her to many corners of the world, including London, New York, South Korea and Taiwan. In March 2005 she represented Scotland at the World Stage Design Competition in Toronto, Canada with Ailsa's costume designs for the play "Spring Awakening?".

Most recently Ailsa had the privilege of designing and making the "Strictly Come Dancing" gowns for The Scottish Sun's Miss Scotland Final 2011. The gowns were worn on the night of the final at Glasgow's Royal Concert Hall and featured in the Scottish Sun Newspaper.

No matter what the project or design, Ailsa is dedicated to providing a first class product. She listens to her clients wishes and provides a unique and professional service that helps complete any special day.

Content:
ABOUT BLISS
BLISS BRIDAL GOWNS OPENED IT’S DOORS FOR THE FIRST TIME IN PERRANPORTH, CORNWALL AT THE BEGINNING OF 2005 AND HAS SINCE GONE FROM STRENGTH TO STRENGTH WITH SPECIAL PRIDE BEING TAKEN IN THE SERVICE THAT WE OFFER.

Bliss Bridal Gowns is now in its 10th year and has always been run on an appointment only basis, this offers every bride to have a personal, relaxed experience with undivided attention. We know every bride and wedding is unique, and we appreciate the importance of listening, caring and working with you to find your perfect dress. Bliss Bridal Gowns is very proud and honoured to have dressed hundreds of brides and their bridesmaids for their big day, we have an excellent reputation and pride ourselves on our superior customer service.

Title: Susan Strachan, Skin & Brow Specialist
Content:
As one of the most highly qualified practitioners in Aberdeen, Susan Strachan loves to learn and ensure her skills are kept updated – meaning every customer benefits from her advanced knowledge and the very latest creative techniques.

Susan specialises in three areas Dermalogica Skin Care, HD Brows and Makeup and is a certified Dermalogica Skin Expert and is one of only a handful of specialists in the UK to hold a post-graduate diploma in skin care from the International Dermal Institute.

She is the only HD Brows Master Stylist in Aberdeen and the first HD Brows Master Stylist in Scotland.

With several years’ experience of making up brides on their big days, she recently updated her skills with a professional make-up artistry course with celebrity make-up artists.

A former graphic designer, she comes from an artistic background and put herself through her initial training simply as a hobby to learn a new skill, before deciding to give up design work to concentrate on the salon.

Continuous development and training means Susan can offer the very best treatments and advice so that every client leaves the salon looking and feeling amazing.

Title: Rubislaw Studio
Content:
Thanks for visiting our page!

Aberdeen wedding photographer Rubislaw Studio is one of the longest established photography studios in Aberdeen. owned and operated by Graham and Jill Noble. We provide stunning wedding images to capture the joy of your special day. 

It all began at the Aberdeen Camera Club, more than 20 years ago, when Graham was asked if he would be interested in training as a wedding photographer with a local studio Martin Johnston. Over the next two years, Graham was trained personally by J.Steve Martin in the classic style of wedding photography which was so popular at in Aberdeen at the time. In fact, many of the successful wedding photographers in the city began by training in the fundamentals of classic photography, and then went on to develop their individual styles.

Incidentally, Martin Johnston were real innovators in photography, and were one of the first studios to provide colour images (when black and white photography was the norm) and  first to bring photographs back to the evening reception of a wedding. Remember that photography was very different back then, and a photographer did not see an image until the film was processed.  

In 1994, Rubislaw Studio was born, when Graham and Jill opened a studio in Carden Place, and soon gained a reputation for producing quality wedding photography and wonderful family portraiture in the new studio.

After six years in Carden Place, and many hundreds of portraits, we decided to relocate the studio to our home in Hamilton Place, and to concentrate on our wedding clients.

We have continued in this way to the present day, with a wedding business which has changed dramatically:

Instead of film we have digital images. This means that we can retouch our images so that everyone looks their best. Traditional albums filled with photographs have been replaced by wonderful storybook albums produced in Italy. Our style of  shooting has changed too, as we moved from the slow film cameras we used (Hasselblad) to the current state of the art digital Canon equipment. 

We cover each wedding with two photographers, so that we able to cover all aspects of the day, with a wonderful mix of classic posed shots, reportage and fine art images. Also, with two photographers, we can be photographing in two places at once!

Our main priority of course is to produce stunning vibrant images which capture the joy of your wedding day. Your images are then beautifully retouched, and we produce a custom album design so that your finished wedding album is a work of art.  

We would be delighted to sit down for a chat one evening to discuss your wedding day photography, and to show you our beautiful display albums by Graphistudio of Italy.

We look forward to hearing from you.

Graham & Jill

Title: Able Photo
Content:
John Doc established his Glasgow Wedding bussines in the millenium year 2000. We can help if you are getting married in Bonnie Scotland. It should be one of the happiest moments in a persons life, however it can become one of the most stressful. Finding and choosing wedding photography companies can be daunting and time consuming, churches, 5e44098b859ec, cars, cakes, rings ect. Aren't you forgetting something?

Think hard! What about hiring a leading Glasgow wedding photography service to ensure you have excellent wedding pictures and DVD, with no staged managed fuss. We are discreet, dedicated and professional wedding DVD photographers with over 12 years experience. Our Scottish family wedding video company comes highly recomended because of our no fuss and unobtrusive style format service.

Also mixing candid, photojournalism and classic traditional wedding photography, John will make formal groups or natural casual candids quickly and efficiently, John has 12 years experience to capture all the very precious moments from your wedding day.

Through out this time John has built a high reputation and has become recommended for being relaxed, informal and no fuss photographer.

Title: Kharaz Jewellery
Content:
Welcome to Kharaz Jewellery.
I make distinctive and original jewellery for those of you who like to stand out from the crowd!
Each piece is individually styled, beads are matched to pendants to create a unique personal statement. There may be similar pieces but no two are ever quite the same.
Travelling to Venice and the island of Murano, I purchase the beautiful glass beads and pendants made there. Each piece is individually made by hand using techniques passed down through generations. The addition of gold or silver leaf really brings the colours to life.
When I return home, I add semi precious stones, crystals, pearls and my own hand made glass beads to produce the original designs shown here.

Travels far and away...
Many of the beads I use are personally chosen by me when on my trips away. I'm always on the lookout for the unusual pieces unique to the places I find them in.
​
The Souk
Take time to check out "The Souk" where you will find an array of beads, pendants and cabochons plus other vintage pieces and curios! Just waiting for you to use in your own jewellery creations... Would love to see what you create with them!

The bigger picture...
Click on individual photos for a close-up look.

Title: AC-Fotoworx
Content:
Based in Cambuslang AC-FotoWorx is a small family run business offering a personal, relaxed and flexible approach to photography.

Having worked for other organisations both here and abroad over the years, in 2009 we decided it was time to open our own family business and AC-FotoWorx was born. This gave us the freedom and opportunity to incorporate our own individuality and modern style in all of our images.

By taking time to fully understand our clients' ideas and desires and encouraging their input we can create unforgetable images that capture the moment perfectly.

By eliminating expensive studio overheads and offering location based photoshoots our clients benefit from affordable photographic services without compromising on quality.

Title: Adorable Cakes
Content:
Here at Adorable Cakes, we are a small friendly run team based in Renfrewshire. We pride ourselves on providing high-quality service and customer satisfaction - we do everything we can to meet your expectations and requirements. Our company is based on the belief that our customers' needs are of the utmost importance. We are committed to meeting those needs and as a result, a high percentage of our business is from repeat customers and referrals.
Feel free to browse through our large selection and variety of cakes for every occasion. We are confident we are able to make exactly what you are looking for, so whether you are looking to choose from our already wide variety, or have something that little bit different in mind, we are here, ready to take your idea and turn it into reality for that special occasion!

Title: Preen Beauty
Content: The rebalance procedure is the replacement of any lost lashes throughout the natural eyelash cycle. The natural eyelash cycle is approximately 90 days; however, each lash is always at a different point in that cycle and will therefore be at different lengths. Preen Beauty eyelash technicians would recommend a monthly rebalance if full eyelash extensions are to be maintained.

Title: AMD Photography
Content:
Professional Commercial & Wedding Photography
Thank you for choosing to view our website and a very warm welcome from the team at AMD Photography. We hope you find all the information you need regarding our commercial photography and wedding photography on this site, however if there is anything you would like to know, please do not hesitate to contact us for more details.

Our Company Vision
Company Director, Anthony M. D'Arcy LMPA, has been extensively involved with commercial photography, wedding photography and multimedia production in Ayrshire, Glasgow and Edinburgh for over 20 years. There is a strong demand for quality professional photography, to that end Anthony created a company which has forged an excellent and widely respected reputation in the field.

Our philosophy is to offer quality without compromise. We create sophisticated images using skilled craftsmanship and the very best technology - in short, we pursue perfection.
We invite you to browse our website to see the range of professional photography services we offer and feel free to contact us with any questions you may have.

Title: Arco Blanco Bridal Couture
Content:
About us

The Arco Blanco Experience

Our philosophy is simple… we believe that buying the most important dress of your life should be a magical, memorable moment. To achieve this, each and every one of our brides is offered a bespoke, professionally tailored service, given the choice of the most stunning, exclusive designs and private use of our beautiful boutique environment in which to experience this.

We are extremely selective about our wedding dresses, and as such we only work with the very best up and coming designers from around the world. We are currently the only bridal store in Scotland to offer Oksana Mukha designs, and indeed one of very few places in the whole of the United Kingdom. This designer’s focus on design and quality is unparalleled. The dresses are perfect examples of high artistic taste, combined with quality and skill, using only the best materials from around the world. The dresses are made of carefully selected quality European fabrics such as silk, taffeta, organza and chiffon, and hand-decorated with complex patterns of pearls, Swarovski crystals, Italian glass and Japanese beading. . We offer a style to suit everyone, from the stylishly simple silhouette to the opulent fairytale extravagance each and every gown we stock has as much personality as you do.

Title: Norwood Hall Hotel
Content:
Macdonald Norwood Hall Hotel was built in 1881 on the site of the 15th Century Pitfodels Castle, offering guests the best in breathtaking Scottish scenery and fine facilities. Conveniently located within easy reach of the historic city centre, Norwood hall Hotel in Aberdeen is a popular choice for anyone visiting Aberdeen on holiday, business or to attend family events such aswedding receptions.

This Aberdeen hotel is a perfect venue for celebrations, events and conferences - Macdonald Norwood Hall Hotel boasts superb guest accommodation and stylish meeting and function rooms, plus breathtaking gardens and surrounding woodland.

Macdonald Norwood Hall Hotel makes an ideal base for country adventures. Roam the beautiful Scottish countryside and marvel in the glorious scenery the Aberdeen area has to offer. And once you've finished exploring, we recommend a visit to our fabulous Tapestry Restaurant to sample some of the fine fare on offer.

Title: Baird & Co
Content:
Baird & Co. Introduction

Baird & Co. was established as a firm in 1967 dealing in numismatic gold coins of the world moving towards volume dealing in bullion gold as government restrictions eased in the 1970s.

By 1975 the business was actively 'making a market' quoting, buying and selling prices for banks, stockbrokers, coin dealers, retail and wholesale jewellers and other volume traders in bullion gold coins, as well as for private clients, becoming one of the UK's leading trading houses of the period.

In 1977 Baird & Co. became the first private contributor to the Reuter Monitor System, giving price indications on a range of bullion coins to banks and dealing rooms world-wide for more than twenty one years on the page code BACO. The latest Internet technology now makes this information available to private investors as well as wholesalers and trade clients through the Baird & Co. web site www.goldline.co.uk

By 1979 the company had progressed into precious metal refining and processing producing a range of carated alloys suitable for the jewellery industry as well as toll refining for clients. The manufacture of precious metal engineered products followed by natural progression and client demand.

Expansion of the company's scrap trading activities necessitated the opening of a branch in the Hatton Garden district in 1987 where over the counter cash trade is still carried out today. Many of the company's products, including a range of gold coins and small bars are also available exclusively to the trade at this branch.

In 1997 Baird & Co. launched the e-commerce Internet website www.goldline.co.uk initially selling bullion coins and investment bars online and supplying private and industry clients with the daily London bullion fixing prices. Goldline developed further in 2001 becoming an innovative platform on which Baird's engineered bullion products are quoted for sale on line direct to clients.

The main processing and manufacturing divisions of the business are now located in more than 30,000 sq.ft of high security premises in Gallions Reach, just five miles east of Canary Wharf and conveniently close to London City Airport.

In September 2000 the company was accepted as a member of the London Bullion Market Association.
