Title: Aberdeen Wedding Shop
Content:
About Us
Aberdeen Wedding Shop started off at a kitchen table making bespoke wedding stationery. Outgrowing the kitchen table it went from there and moved to small premises and then onto the current premises in George Street. Having made stationery for many years a lot of customers were asking us about chair cover and centrepiece hire, being told how much flair and creativity we had helped with the decision so it was a natural evolution of the company to provide these services and the rest is history.

Preferring to be a leader we have strived to achieve the quality of product and generally every month we come up with something new to keep us ahead in the marketplace and also with very competitive prices.

We take vast pride in our work and over the years have received many thank you cards and testimonials, a large amount of our work also comes from referrals and we have a great respect from fellow professionals within the wedding industry.

All the aspects of the business fit perfectly together to make planning your wedding day much easier. Use the services of one product or several, the choice is yours. Your Wedding Day is of utmost importance and with a wealth of experience you can be assured of good guidance and advice to keep you in the right direction. We currently provide stationery, favours, chair cover hire, centrepiece hire, prop hire, balloon artistry and wedding cakes.

Title: Oasis Beauty Clinic
Content:
With the hectic pace of everyday living, we at Oasis offer a haven of tranquilly, to give you the opportunity to make that little bit of time for yourself and give your body and mind that much needed pampering.

You can choose from our wide range of beauty treatments, with superb treatment packages available to suit your requirements. In consultation with one of our highly trained therapists, you can even have a tailor made treatment to meet your individual needs.

We have built up a strong client base over the past nine years and pride ourselves on meeting our clients' needs.

Be sure to visit our Facebook page for more information and regular updates.

Title: Orchid Studio
Content:
AttOrchid Bridal Studio we have over 10years experience in the Bridal Industry and pride ourselves in being The One Stop Bridal Shop. Offering a selection of Designer Gowns by Justin Alexnader, Sincerity, Enzoni, Eternity and Bellice. The new 2015/16 gowns are now in store including our fabulous Bridesmaids collections by designers Kelsey Rose and Veromia.

After you have chosen your dream dress and beautiful bridesmaids gowns its time to choose your Wedding Flowers -- Wedding Cake -- Venue Styling including Chair Covers -- Backdrop -- Candy Cart and many other 5e4401d23d861 to keep your guests in awe the whole day through. We will also help you choose a theme for your special day and have this running from beginning to end so your Wedding Day is everything you could have wished for.

Our award winning florist can work with the simple elegant look to the more flamboyant, from churches and chapels to registry offices or civil ceremonies. The flowers can then be transfered to the reception and used to decorate the function room at your choosen venue.

When it comes to your Wedding Cake our award winning designer will create a cake to compliment your chosen theme or if you prefer something totally different then he will design one to your liking with flavours to tempt every pallet.

We have recently opened a Sale Room with ex-sample dresses at much reduced prices.

Orchid Bridal Studio operate by appointment only, so please call us to arrange this in advance on 028 38 392121

Orchid Studio 115-117 Bridge Street, Portadown, Co Armagh, BT63 5AA

Title: Premier Marquees
Content:
Premier Marquees provide a complete marquee hire service throughout Ireland and Northern Ireland - ideal for weddings, agricultural shows, sporting events, functions, corporate entertainment and more.

Our marquees are modern aluminium framed, clear span structures and completely free standing. They can be erected on any surface - hard, soft, lawn, concrete or they can be erected flush against exterior walls, on patios and driveways.

We can cater for a wide range of events from small garden parties to large corporate events - anything from 15 guests to over 1,000 at a wedding! Marquees are a specialty an we have all sizes for all occasions !

Title: Sew Good
Content:
Sew good offers a fantastic dressmaking service including made-to-measure and full clothes alterations.

No job is to big or small for us. We are educated seamstress with many years experience.

Our shop has a quick service and a relaxed and comfortable atmosphere.

No job is to big or small for Sew good!

  • If your favourite clothes don't fit or need repairing, we can help.
  • What about those classic items that you just can't do without? We can re-make them.
  • Are you going to the party, pram or wedding? We can make something especially for you.
  • Wedding? Don't panic! We offer a height quality work on bridal alterations to make you Big Day a perfect.
  • We also repair, alter and make home furnishing to you requirements e.g. curtains, cushion covers, bed linen, etc.
  • Want to shortening jeans and keep the Original Hem? It's the right place

Title: Stacey Kilpatrick Make-Up
Content:
Stacey Angeline Kilpatrick is the S.A.K. behind S.A.K.DESIGNS!
A mum of two and lover of all things small, cute or sparkly.

Stacey grew up dreaming of becoming a professional makeup artist and started her own face painting company, Crazy Faces, when she was just 21.

Now a multi award winning professional makeup artist, Stacey has trained in Belfast and London, competed at international level and become a well-known name in the makeup industry as well as in the face painting world across Ireland.  

Although Stacey’s roots lie in face and body painting, her true passion is bridal makeup.  She says: “There is something extra special about playing such an important role in a wedding; sharing the laughs, tears and nerves and helping things to run smoothly and make people feel at their best.”

S.A.K. DESIGNS is based in Glenanne, County Armagh but Stacey regularly travels across Northern Ireland, Southern Ireland and the UK mainland, bringing a little bit of makeup magic to her clients.

Amazon Hairdressing
Content:
At Amazon Hairdressing we have a passion for beautiful hairstyles. We pride ourselves on delivering the highest standards of customer care and attention to detail for each individual.

When visiting Amazon Hairdressing our artistic team of stylists are highly trained and motivated in all aspects of hairdressing for ladies, gents and children, ensuring our clients receive the best possible hairdressing experience.

Title: Andrew Watson Menswear Ltd
Content:
Andrew Watson has been in the clothing business as long as he can remember. Having started with the Boyce family at Copperfield in the mid 70's Andrew has always had a passion for good cloth and excellent cut. Since opening his own store in 2010 he has travelled extensively throughout Europe with Tim on the search for the best in mens clothing. He and the team have bought in a number of new designers not showcased on the island, and only available in a handful of mainland stores.
The store is a firm favourite with regulars and is also now firmly on the list for tourist destinations for things to do in Belfast.

Title: Craftworld
Content:
Craftworld is a treasure trove for all you crafty and creative people. Whether you are making a gift for a loved one, customising your clothes or just need some inspiration for a project, we have an abundance of craft supplies.
Craftworld has thousands of arts & crafts products – everything you need- whether you are making your own organic soap, knitting a stylish garment, or creating your unique wedding invitations, we have it all here!!
Craftworld (originally a department in Northern Ireland’s best known toy shop- Leisureworld) was established in 1976. It has been run as a family business, fuelling the creativity of the people of Northern Ireland and as far away as Dubai for over 35 years. We are located in the heart of our city so pop in for a chat with one of our friendly staff who are more than happy to help with your projects, ideas & imaginations.

Title: Darragh Casey Photography
Content:
My name is Darragh Casey, I'm a Northern Ireland Wedding Photographer and I love photographing couples on their wedding day. Capturing your wedding day with my creative wedding photography style, while you enjoy your day with family and friends.

Documentary wedding photography is all about telling a story through pictures. It’s about being as unobtrusive as possible, letting the day flow naturally, without manipulation. As a reportage wedding photographer I work quietly and discreetly, which allows me to capture the real moments of a wedding day. All those special moments as they unfold, from the excitement of getting ready through to the first dance. Your wedding is a once-in-a-lifetime event that should be photographed and documented with complete respect to the events unfolding.

I'm passionate about what I do. I love watching the day unfold through my camera lens, and making beautiful photographs that can transport you right back to the moment they were taken.

If you would like a few family group shots I am happy to photograph these, I work quickly so they don’t intrude too much on your day. My portraits of the bride and groom are shot in a very relaxed manner - I’ll not ask you to do any silly poses! I’ll make you feel relaxed in front of the camera, you’ll trust me to let yourselves have a few intimate moments together.

By booking me as your wedding photograher, you can simply relax and enjoy your day with family and friends without having to worry about photographs. Please refer to the Wedding Information section for more details, and answers to commonly asked questions regarding my wedding photography.

Please enjoy viewing my wedding photographs in the Featured Wedding and Gallery sections, you can view more of my work on my Blog.

If you would like me to tell the story of your wedding day please give me a call, all my details can be found on my Contact Page.

Title: David Coote Photography
Content:
Northern Ireland wedding photographer, David Coote embarked on his professional photography career after leaving college. Over the past 20 years David has established a reputation for producing high quality wedding images at competitive prices.

David is based in Ballygowan, County Down. Being only a short drive from Belfast and close to Newtownards, Bangor and the surrounding area, David is in the ideal location for both town and country weddings.

David is renowned for his relaxed friendly manner and his ability to maintain a good rapport with his clients. With a unique approach to each wedding David’s flair and enthusiasm produces natural images which reflect the happy mood of that special day.

David has succeeded in meeting the high standards demanded by the British Institute of Professional Photography and the Professional Photographers Association of Northern Ireland and is a qualified member of both.

David is an active member of PPANI and is currently serving on Council.

Title: I Do Wedding
Content:
Do Wedding Boston

The I Do Wedding Boston team prides itself in providing a unique, fun, and memorable shopping experience. Whether you are coming in for dresses , photography packages, hair & makeup services, or wedding planning, we want you to walk out with a sense of accomplishment and a smile.

Consider us a one-stop-shop for your wedding day needs. Whether your wedding be intimate or extravagant we have the connections to capture your wedding dream. It’s important for us that our couples have a sound mind and can plan their wedding effortlessly.

As a local business we want to expand our network by partnering up with other local businesses around the metro Boston area. It is a means for us to create a sense of community within the Boston bridal industry. If there is anything we learned about what makes for a flawless and successful wedding, is that team-work and communication between wedding vendors is key. A wedding is not possible without everyone’s combined efforts and expertise.

Title: I Do Wedding Stationery & Venue Styling
Content:
Hi, welcome to I do Wedding Stationery & Venue Styling

Welcome to I do Weddings’ website. We are very excited to show you some of our products and to showcase everything we have to offer.

With over 8 years experience in the wedding industry, I do Wedding are one of Northern Irelands leading Wedding and events specialists.

We cater for weddings small and large and provide a wide range of venue dressing services including Chair Covers, Sparkle Backdrops, Sparkle Table Skirting, Drapes, Lighting, Table centre pieces, Thrones and LED Dancefloors. We also stock finishing touches such as balloons, Table scatter crystals, gifts for the bridal party and favours.

I do Wedding specialise in creating luxury and stunning handmade wedding invitations and matching stationery. We use only the highest quality of cards and ribbons. All our invitations are handcrafted and we offer a bespoke Wedding Stationery service where you can come to us with your ideas and we can create something unique for you. We also supply card and materials for people wishing to make stationery themselves.

If you are looking for that something a little different for your wedding reception why not take a look at our mobile Ice Cream Bicycle, our Victorian Popcorn and Candyfloss cart , our Vintage Candy Cart, or even our Slush machines.

We hope you enjoy looking at our website and we look forward to hearing from you soon. Remember to like our facebook page to stay uptodate with all the latest news and offers and also to see lots more photos.

Rachel xx

Title: Limpley Stoke Hotel
Content: Overlooking Limpley Stoke valley, this classic hotel in a stone-built Georgian mansion is 4 miles from the Roman Baths and 5 miles from Royal Crescent. Country house-style rooms feature free Wi-Fi and flat-screen TVs, as well as tea and coffee making facilities. Some offer valley views. Upgraded rooms have 4-poster beds, Bluetooth speakers and/or free drinks. Full English breakfast is complimentary. There's a traditional restaurant serving British cuisine and a cosy bar with a valley-view terrace. Other amenities include a garden with a gazebo, free parking and event facilities.

Title: The Old Mill Hotel
Content: The Old Mill Hotel in Bath is beautifully located by the River Avon. There are 35 lovely bedrooms,  banqueting suites and a delightful restaurant by the river with a unique waterwheel feature. Most of the bedrooms, banqueting rooms, restaurant and bars have stunning views of the River Avon and the beautiful countryside surrounding it. Title: Dukes Hotel
Content:
ABOUT DUKES LONDON

Nestled in the heart of historic St. James’s Mayfair, DUKES LONDON is a sophisticated, luxury hotel where you will arrive as a guest and leave as a friend.

Ever since King Henry 8th built his palace here in the 16th Century, St. James’s has been the exclusive retreat of writers, musicians, politicians and royalty.

Whether you choose to stay in one of our modern or classic style bedrooms or luxurious suites, unwind in the legendary DUKES Bar, savour our Great British Restaurant, or embrace true English chic with Champagne afternoon tea, we promise you an enthusiastic team, dedicated entirely to making your time here exceptional.

We look forward to welcoming you on your next visit to London.

Title: Artistry in Sugar
Content:
History of Mells

Mells is famous for its lovely architecture, ancient streets and dramatic location. There are many things to do in Mells – visit the ancient church and churchyard, enjoy the walled garden and country walks and, of course, relax in the village Café or the newly refurbished Talbot Inn.

History is what underpins all of this and we are fortunate to have a fascinating history of the village and the Horner and Asquith family (who have lived in the Manor House in its various forms since the 16th century)  written for this site by the current Earl of Oxford and Asquith, Raymond Oxford….

MELLS can trace its history from the Mesolithic flint workshops (ca. 6,000 BC) found on the down to the north of the village, and the Neolithic (ca 2,000 BC) fortresses that are positioned in echelon, guarding the entrances of its valleys. Archaeology has shown that Tedbury Camp, to the east, was part of the same ‘kingdom’, or defensive system, that is dominated by Dolebury Camp above Burrington Combe and the Bristol Channel.

Several British villas (200 BC-400 AD) are located on the south slopes of the down and there are Roman camps on Newbury Hill and in Hobblyground field to the north of the Manor House. The remains of a Roman village has been found along the stream from Branch Farm to the ruined cottage at Quarry Close.

A Saxon village existed around the upper pond at Branch, Saxon jewellery has been found in the Iron Valley and even a ceremonial Danish axehead. In 942 AD the Saxon King Edmund granted land at Mells to Count Athelstan who in turn gave it to Glastonbury Abbey. It was Glastonbury that built most of the medieval part of the village, including the Tithe Barn, Bilboa House, New Street, Selwood House and part of The Talbot inn.

Title: The Barn at Wick Farm
Content:
Perfect Wedding Venue for Bath

Wick Farm is a medieval farm steeped in history and built for the monks at nearby Hinton Priory. Dating from 1372 it is set in 37 acres of stunning countryside, complete with horses, sheep, pigs, chickens and even a duck pond.

The beautiful threshing barn with views of the Westbury White Horse could not be a better rural retreat for your special day.

Just off the A36, sandwiched between Bath, Bristol, Chippenham, Warminster and Frome with ample parking and full wheel chair access into both barns, Wick Farm makes the perfect venue for your wedding, party, conference or meeting.

Title: Zone Imaging
Content:
Hi,I'm Darren. Im a photographer, husband & father (although maybe not in that order!). Im humbled that you have taken the time to view my work and learn a bit more about myself and my style of photography.

Weddings are such amazing, emotional & fun celebrations (ok, maybe a little stressful for you, but trust me everything will be ok & I will help you through it). My role is to capture all of this through my lens. I see myself as a guest at each wedding I photograph, the only difference being is that I'm a guest with a few cameras and lenses!

My way of seeing is to tell a Story of each day's events whether this is the Mehndi, Nikkah, Baraat or any other event & to give you a set of images that will show your Story unfold. I like to capture all the little details, the emotions of the day and all the traditions and customs. I am definitely not a photographer that likes to stand still. I like to listen to what you want from your wedding and then we can work together to build your pictures.

A good place to start to view my work would be on the Blog section of my site. Here you can see the Stories I have already told with a selection of images from my previous clients.

All that is left to say is to thank you for considering myself to be part of your Wedding Story. If you would like to get in contact with myself for an initial consultation please feel free to email or drop me a call.

Title: Culloden Estate & Spa
Content: Set in a grand 19th-century mansion on 12 acres of grounds, this high-end spa hotel is an 11-minute walk from Belfast Lough and 6.5 miles from Titanic Belfast museum. Traditionally styled rooms feature desks, flat-screen TVs and iPod docks, plus tea and coffee making facilities. Suites add marble bathrooms and separate living areas. The spa features an indoor pool with a whirlpool spa, a steam room and a gym. Dining options include an upscale restaurant, a refined lounge bar serving afternoon tea, and a bistro. There's also a function suite and 5 meeting rooms. Free WiFi is available.

Title: I Do Wedding Stationery & Venue Styling
Content:
Welcome to I do Weddings’ website. We are very excited to show you some of our products and to showcase everything we have to offer.

With over 8 years experience in the wedding industry, I do Wedding are one of Northern Irelands leading Wedding and events specialists.

We cater for weddings small and large and provide a wide range of venue dressing services including Chair Covers, Sparkle Backdrops, Sparkle Table Skirting, Drapes, Lighting, Table centre pieces, Thrones and LED Dancefloors. We also stock finishing touches  such as balloons, Table scatter crystals, gifts for the bridal party and favours.

I do Wedding specialise in creating luxury and stunning handmade wedding invitations and matching stationery. We use only the highest quality of cards and ribbons. All our invitations are handcrafted and we offer a bespoke Wedding  Stationery service where you can come to us with your ideas and we can create something unique for you. We also supply card and materials for people wishing to make stationery themselves.

If you are looking for that something a little different for your wedding reception why not take a look at our mobile Ice Cream Bicycle, our Victorian Popcorn and Candyfloss cart , our Vintage Candy Cart, or even our Slush machines.

We hope you enjoy looking at our website and we look forward to hearing from you soon. Remember to like our facebook page to stay uptodate with all the latest news and offers and also to see lots more photos.

Rachel xx

Title: The Clarion Hotel
Content:
The contemporary Clarion Hotel Carrickfergus offers a panoramic view of Belfast from many bright guestrooms. Renovated in 2005, the hotel combines international architecture with ultimate comfort.

Due to a prime location of Clarion Hotel Carrickfergus, guests have direct access to St. Nicholas Church, U.S. Rangers Centre and Theatre At The Mill. Parliament Buildings Stormont, Bangor Marina and Harland and Wolff Cranes - Samson and Goliath in Belfast are located nearby.

The hotel is surrounded by bars and restaurants.

Guests can reach Clarion Hotel Carrickfergus by car from George Best Belfast City airport in 15 minutes.

Title: JK Photography Video Production
Content:
JK Photography & Video has been established for over 21 years and specialise in all kinds of occasions from weddings to birthday parties and much more.

We offer a complete range of solutions for any occassion and understand that your occassion is an once in a lifetime experience, and so we are truly passionate about creating memories that you can cherish for a lifetime.

All our images are taken in RAW on a full frame professional DSLR cameras and our Video is done on a full frame HD 1080i and up to 4K recording, we also provide our service on Cinematic recording using the DSLR to captutre the essence of your special occasion. Our aim is to capture moments as they occur naturally, so that you have a true reflection of the day.

NOW we also offer Video Cranes and drone for Aerial Videography shooting in full HD 1080i or up to 4K recording.

NB: We also provide our services for the corporate and commercial sector.

Our company is based in West Yorkshire and we cover all parts of the UK.

Title: Lagan Valley Island
Content:
Situated on an island in the heart of Lisburn city, Lagan Valley Island is one of Northern Ireland's premier venues.

The site on which Lagan Valley Island was built once played a significant role in Lisburn's industrial past. Previously the site for the Island Mill Spinning Company, famous for the production on linen through it, production at the Mill came to an end in 1983. When this happened, Lisburn City Council (then Lisburn Borough Council) purchased the site and with funding assistance from the National Lottery to the Arts Council of Northern Ireland, regeneration of this site began.

The building opened for business in March 2001 and was officially opened in November 2001 by Her Majesty the Queen. Lagan Valley Island has many functions; It is headquarters of Lisburn & Castlereagh City Council and the facility is also a unique mix of civic, business and arts facilities - home to council offices, the Island Arts Centre, Council Chambers, a purpose built Conference Centre, Theatre, and stunning wedding facilities

Title: Brian Harte Photography
Content:
Not people standing stock-still like soldiers on parade, or grinning unnaturally, or being on their best behaviour. Just people being themselves. Laughing, smiling, playing, talking, dancing and running. Doing all the things that people do.
It's called photojournalism. It's the difference between being second row up, third from the left, and just being yourself, with all the little things that make you different.
Go on. Be yourself.

Title: Black Mill Photography
Content:
Hi, thanks for visiting my website! I’m Jonny Paine, a West Yorkshire based wedding photographer, specializing in documentary wedding photography. My informal and relaxed photojournalistic approach creates honest, fun and timeless photographs that capture real moments, real emotions and the genuine atmosphere of your day.

This genre of photography is all about telling a story. It’s about weaving beautiful and natural images together to tell the tale of your wedding day.

Please take a look at some of my featured weddings in the galleries section to see my standard of work. Although predominantly I cover West Yorkshire, I am also happy to travel near and far to capture your wedding day. If you would like to keep up to date with my latest weddings and news, please follow me on Facebook.

Please do not hesitate to get in touch to find out more about what we offer and our pricing.

Thanks

Title: Atmosphere Media
Content:
Hello, my name is Paul Harper and I’d like to welcome you to the Atmosphere Media Productions website. The company was formed eight years ago in response to a growing public demand for professional multimedia services, here in the UK.

In that time we have developed an outstanding entertainments service. This is backed up by our state of the art event and media recording facilities in Photographic, Audio, Video and DVD formats. A small sample of our products can be found in the Recent Projects section.

Title: The Perfect Party Setup
Content: Twin sisters Laura Gault and Susan McCarter have been working together in the party industry since 2011.  The story began, and continues, with the girls selling party supplies for baby showers, childrens birthdays, christenings and engagement parties.  As their business started to grow so did their knowledge of how to set up the perfect party.  With numerous enquiries for wedding supplies laura and Susan decided to expand their party expertise and join the wedding industry.  Neither of the girls have looked back and enjoy decorating weddings as much as they do a beautiful baby shower or a fun 3rd birthday.

Title: Daniel Burton Photography
Content:
l-burton.co.uk
We specialise in ground and high level architectural photography which is also known as mast or pole photography. Our form of architectural photography allows us to capture stunning high level photographs of commercial buildings and sites. Our style of photography provides commercial clients a chance to capture stunning high level photographs of company premises, projects or things of interest. We capture high quality digital images from a range of heights that capture the built environment.

Please take a look around our site and view our portfolio, where you will find a large selection of architectural photography work that we have carried out over the years. Working with a number of major UK companies we have experience of a wide range of architectural projects.

Our previous work has taken us all over the UK and around the world using our high level photography methods. We have invested in high quality equipment including high end digital cameras and a range of telescopic masts that operate at extreme heights. Our range of photography masts allow us to capture high quality architectural photos at a range of heights while maintaining full control of the photography equipment.

Title: Stormont Hotel
Content:
THE STORMONT HOTEL - FROM HOUSE TO HOTEL

The hotel has risen like a phoenix from the fire. Purchased in 1966 by Sir William Hastings, it was originally a large period house and home to the McMaster family. The 10 bedroom home was quickly converted into a hotel, in order to secure a liquor license – hugely important, as it was the only place to get a drink in the area, for several miles.

Somewhat typically, this move proved hugely successful. After several major renovations and extensions, the hotel now boasts 105 luxurious bedrooms, 15 private conference and banqueting suites and choice of two restaurants.

The spacious grounds and ample car parking also make it one of Northern Ireland’s first choices for conference and exhibition business.

Title: Hastings Hotels Group Ltd
Content:
Hastings Hotels in Northern Ireland - the local hotel chain which has stayed upbeat through thick and thin!

Hastings Hotels is the largest independent hotel group in Northern Ireland with seven luxurious properties across the province. This family owned company was established in the late 1960's.  Over the past 30 years has introduced all four of his children to the group in the roles of Managing Director, Sales Director, Marketing Director and Events Director. It has not been an easy fifty years for Sir William and his group of hotels, and despite numerous setbacks and obstacles over the years, the company has continued to grow and grow.

Title: Ivanhoe Inn & Hotel
Content:
The bright and modern 70-seater Grill and Bar Restaurant begins food service from 7.00am - 9.30pm Monday - Saturday and 7.00am - 8.30pm Sunday.  Presenting mouth watering dishes, our chefs work hard to keep up to date with current food trends.  Menus are changed seasonally to make the most of the wide range of local ingredients now available.  The choice of delicious specials are changed daily and are extremely popular with all our customers.

Our Wine List includes wines which have been carefully selected by our chosen partners Direct Wine Shipments, to accompany our wonderful food.

Title: Dylan McBurney Photography
Content: Dylan McBurney is a Northern Ireland wedding photographer who has shot award-winning images both in Ireland and around Europe in places like London, Barcelona, Paris, and Prague. His boutique wedding studio has delivered over 200 beautiful custom designed wedding books to clients in Ireland and the UK. Inspired by legendary photographer Henri Cartier-Bresson, Dylan's simple, romantic, natural light images focus on the bride and groom’s interactions with friends and family, often revealing powerful emotions and relationships and capturing the uncomplicated charm of stolen glances or guests laughing. Dylan has been a member of the prestigious Wedding Photojournalist Association (WPJA) since 2009 and his work has been exhibited in the Culture Project Gallery in New York, La Salle de la Mairie, St Brieuc, France and at the Université de Rennes, France.

Title: Wedding Dayz
Content:
Many couples say their day rushes by in a blur. Trust us to capture that day and preserve those memories. Our filming is discrete and natural, so we capture those candid moments.
No ordinary wedding video company. We pride ourselves on doing things a little different. At wedding dayz you will not get what we would term a traditional wedding video. Your wedding is one of the most important days of your life. Re-live your day over and over again.
We are a Professional video company who offer stylish modern wedding videos. Having working in the industry for over 15 years we have seen wedding videos almost identical in appearance. We are proud offer something different. Our discrete approach ensures a natural and spontaneous outcome.
We also believe other wedding video companies over change for their services. You will not be over charged here and no quality will be compromised. We offer a simple approach to pricing. No extra money for this or that - you know exactly what your getting beforehand.

Title: Belfast Castle
Content: Belfast Castle is set on the slopes of Cavehill Country Park, Belfast, Northern Ireland in a prominent position 400 feet above sea level. Its location provides unobstructed views of the city of Belfast and Belfast Lough.

Title: Old Yeller Paper Co
Content: Old Yeller Paper Co. is a boutique stationery brand, created by illustrator Dee Mullan. We are based in Belfast, Northern Ireland and our line of custom wedding stationery features Dee's charming and timeless illustrations. She works closely with her clients to create beautiful hand-painted stationery which reflects the unique character of each wedding.

Title: Belfast Harlequins
Content:
About Belfast Harlequins

A cross community, multi-sports club situated on 15 acres of magnificent pitches in the heart of South Belfast, playing rugby, hockey, squash and bowls. Each year our facilities are used extensively with an annual footfall in excess of 80,000 making Belfast Harlequins the premier, cross community sports club on the island of Ireland!

Title: Status Wedding Cars Ltd
Content:
WELCOME
Status Wedding Cars have a unique range of wedding packages designed to offer you the perfect service for your special day. We have a full fleet of Mercedes vehicles to cater for both primary wedding car transport as well as transport options for groups and guests.
OUR VEHICLES
We have a range of luxury modern Mercedes wedding vehicles to choose from, with offices based in both Newcastle and Teesside we can provide our services right across the North East. We are able to cater for any number of guests and can tailor our wedding packages to suit your individual requirements

OUR CHAUFFEURS
Our wedding cars come with a professionally trained chauffeur who will tend to your every need. You will be collected from your home or pick up address, taken to the service venue, your chauffeur will wait during the service and for photographs before proceeding onto the reception venue.

Title: Park Avenue Hotel
Content: This stylish hotel is a 9-minute walk from The Arches Centre and 2.1 miles from George Best Belfast City Airport. The contemporary rooms and suites feature flat-screen TVs and free WiFi, as well as tea and coffee making equipment. Suites add fireplaces, separate living areas and iPod docks. There's an on-site bar serving light bites and a white-tablecloth restaurant dishing out continental cuisine. Other amenities include 14 meeting rooms, an exercise room and free guest parking.

Title: Europa Hotel
Content: Situated opposite the Grand Opera House, this contemporary hotel is a 3-minute walk from Great Victoria Street train station and a 12-minute walk from Victoria Square Shopping Centre. The sophisticated rooms and suites feature free WiFi, flat-screen TVs, iPod docks, as well as tea and coffee making equipment. Some rooms have mountain or city views, and suites add mini fridges and separate living areas. There's a chic bistro, a bar and a piano lounge on-site. Other amenities include 17 meeting rooms and a 1,200-person event space.

Title: Peter Thomas Photography
Content:
I’ve had a keen interest in photography since my childhood. Photography remained a big part of what I did and what inspired me. When I was asked by friends to shoot their wedding in Edinburgh I jumped at the chance. I enjoyed myself so much that this became the starting point of my career.

It’s hard to believe, but that first wedding was way back in 2005! After that first wedding, things started to snowball. I got asked by friends to do weddings, and then friends of friends. Word soon got around! After a while I decided to concentrate on wedding photography full time.

More recently, I’ve expanded into portrait and commercial photography. I opened our Belfast studio in 2011 and have since welcomed many families through the door.

Title: Digital Bride Wedding Photography
Content:
Our photography department is headed by our Director of Photography, William Bittles LPPANI SWPP. William has developed a style that sets Digital Bride apart from the mainstream wedding photographer in Northern Ireland. His passion and enthusiasm for photography are reflected in unique and timeless images, working with your family and friends to capture the full range of emotions that you and your guests experience during the day. William has a relaxed professional approach that puts our couples at ease. This easygoing manner endears him to his clients, leading to comfortable, fun and creative wedding day. William is a liceniate of The Professional Photographers Association of Northern Ireland (PPANI). The PPANI was founded in 1966 and from then the Association has progressed from strength to strength, holding conferences and seminars. The result being they offer the public some of the highest standards of work in The United Kingdom which has a strict Code of Ethics that is rigidly enforced to ensure the consumer is not only hiring a talented photographer, but also one with impeccable business practices and who are are fully insured for Public Liability and Professional Indemnity, giving you peace of mind and something less to worry about on your special day.

William is also a member of the UK wide, Society of Wedding and Portrait Photographers (SWPP)

Title: Sparkles
Content:
Sparkles is a family run business based in Sunderland serving the Wedding and Party requirements of the North East of England.Our services include Handcrafted Wedding and Party Stationery, Balloons, Chocolate Fountain, Fruit Palm Trees, Candy Station, Chair Cover Hire and our Starlight Backdrop.
Our aim is always to offer unrivalled levels of service, competitively priced without any compromise on quality. We are constantly looking to innovate to offer our customers new and exiting ideas for their special event. We are trusted suppliers to many of the biggest and best venues in the area.

Title: The Merchant Hotel
Content: Housed in a former bank, this grand Victorian and art deco-style hotel is a 4-minute walk from St. Anne's Cathedral and 1.7 miles from Crescent Arts Centre. The sophisticated rooms and suites feature flat-screen TVs, WiFi access and mini fridges, as well as tea and coffee making equipment. Suites add separate living rooms; some also have fireplaces. There is a spa and a rooftop gym with panoramic views of the city, as well as 6 meeting rooms. Dining and nightlife options include a white-tablecloth restaurant, a nightclub and a jazz bar.

Title: Donard Hotel
Content:
THE DONARD

"Where the Mountains of Mourne sweep down to the sea" Located in Newcastle at the foot of the beautiful Mourne Mountains the Donard Hotel is ideally situated for a great family holiday, a relaxing weekend break, business or private event. An established family run hotel, the Donard Hotel provides its guests with the highest standards of comfort and hospitality in a relaxed and friendly atmosphere. Comprising of 18 comfortable bedrooms, the hotel’s accommodation has been tastefully decorated to maintain that home away from home feeling. All rooms are en-suite and have television, telephone, tea & coffee facilities and iron and trouser press.Fully licensed, the Chapters Restaurant and PM Coffee Shop serve good food all day. The Donard also has a lift service ands provides excellent facilities for the less able bodied. As a renowned seaside resort Newcastle has something to offer everyone - golf, fishing, pony trekking, walking and of course spectacular scenery. To make your visit truly memorable be our guest at the Donard Hotel - a warm welcome awaits you.

Title: Five Star Travel UK Ltd

Title: Purple Violets Floristry
Content:
Purple Violets Floristry is based in Kingswood, Bristol.

Working from our studio, we enjoy creating a range of floral designs, from tributes to express your love & feelings at a time of loss, to creating the wedding flowers of your dreams to celebrate the most special day of your life.

We also create beautiful bouquets & arrangements for other occasions including Birthdays, anniversaries, new baby, Christmas, Valentines Day & Mother’s Day.

Same day delivery is available.
For more information or to order call us on 07511928110 or online

Title: Champagne Vintage Cars
Content:
Our selection of vintage wedding cars have been hand picked to provide you with the best selection of vehicles for your wedding transport.

All our vintage cars and wedding limos are matching in old English white giving you the opportunity to add the colour of ribbons and bows of your choice to suit on your special day.

You may choose to travel back in time with the 1933 vintage Rolls Royce wedding car which is capable of transporting any happy couple in comfort and style ensuring an unparalleled safety and star treatment from the moment we arrive. Alternatively the Beauford 1930's open top tourer is one of the most stunning and impressive convertible cars available. The Daimler 7 seater laundelette limousine is also a very popular wedding car for bridesmaids and page boys.

We provide wedding transport services from as little as one hour up to full day hires. Please do not hesitate to call at any time and speak any one of our helpful staff on 0800 316 7588 we are here to help and give as much advice you need on planning the transport for your special day.

Please note: obtaining the cheapest quotation for your vintage wedding transport, on one of the most memorable days of your life is not necessarily the best answer, please take time to come to us and view the vintage wedding cars that we have available on this website.

Title: Warmley Community Centre
Content:
The Centre is a long established focal point for the community of Warmley. It is a spacious
building offering a variety of different sized rooms for hire (full details here). The building is located on the A420 Bristol – Chippenham Road adjacent to the ring road. This location offers easy access to North Bristol and South Gloucestershire. The Centre has a large, well-lit car park giving level easy access to the centre itself.

The Centre is the meeting place for numerous activities details of which can be found here. All rooms are available for private hire at very reasonable rates. Why not hold your wedding reception, birthday, anniversary or child’s party at the centre, it beats having a mess at home! You can use the large kitchen to do your own catering or we can provide caterers at a reasonable cost.

Title: Sandon Hall & Park Enterprises
Content:
THE CEREMONY

One of the best loved wedding venues
in Staffordshire.

Sandon Hall is one of the most sought-after wedding venues in Staffordshire. The country mansion’s magnificent interior and picturesque gardens make it the perfect location for a wedding, civil partnership ceremony, or reception. The ancestral home of the Harrowby family, we look forward to hosting your big day.

With a range of stunning backdrops, from our stunning gardens or our very own 13th century All Saints church, you can choose the perfect location for your big day. Sandon Church is perfect for those wanting a traditional church wedding, and is only a short drive—or carriage ride—from the house.

Title: Park Hall Farm Wedding Venue
Content:
Do you want to make a strong impression on your clients or customers? Park Hall Farm Wedding Venue is your answer. Our grade II listed farmhouse set in beautifully landscaped gardens, complete with a moat and waterfall is the ideal choice for you to hold an event of any size that will surely get everyone's attention.
For conference venue hire near Stoke-on-Trent call Park Hall Farm Wedding Venue on 07914 004 634 today.
Whether your event is an exhibition, seminar, corporate hospitality, training or team building, our conference venue is the perfect choice for you. We have one meeting room to the front of the house which can accommodate 2 to 10 people which is suitable for smaller presentations.

For larger presentations and seminars, we can accommodate 2 to 400 people in our marquee set in our beautiful gardens. The marquee is fully heated with projection, screens and microphones to assist with your presentations and speeches. For more information on our services and wedding venue hire get in touch with us.

Title: Chocolate Tailor
Content:
With attention to detail and style, The Chocolate Tailor produces a range of delicious chocolates tailored to your chocoholic needs. Based in North Staffordshire, delicious chocolates by The Chocolate Tailor can be sourced at farmers' markets and events in Staffordshire, Shropshire, Derbyshire and Cheshire. The Chocolate Tailor also offers a bespoke service for collection - please see the Diary of Events page to see venues.

The Chocolate Tailor provides bespoke chocolates for lots of occasions and clients. Each item is not mass-produced; not found on the High Street - it is something unique.

Gift boxes personalised to your taste with ribbon, raffia, and flower décor
Small token boxes in a range of shapes and colours – just to say ‘thank you’ or ‘welcome home’.
Wedding, party or dinner favours, attractively decorated to fit your scheme
Children’s fun gifts and party favours boxes
Seasonal presents – Christmas, Valentine’s Day, Mother’s Day, Easter, Father’s Day – designed to be different
Chocolate parties – a fun way to taste chocolates in the company of friends
Corporate gifts for clients; an opportunity to enhance business goodwill
Hotels, restaurants, event and wedding planners; bespoke after-dinner

Title: Memorable Occasions
Content:
Why Memorable Occasions?

There is no better way to honor the accomplishments or life’s milestones of a family member or close friend than to host an event that celebrates their special day with the people they love most. These are memories they will cherish forever! A wedding, anniversary, birthday or mitzvah celebration can make a huge impression on the person being acknowledged and convey a feeling of admiration for the thoughtful host of the party. Don’t trust the planning and organization of your Mission Viejo,CA celebrations to just anyone. These special events only happen once and they need to be as reflective of what you want as if you had the time and know-how to do it yourself.

Title: The Handcrafted Card Co.Ltd,
Content:
After frequent requests from our clients we launched our new ranges of greeting cards early in 2004.

This was an exciting venture for us - we use the same philosophy for our greeting cards as we do for our handmade wedding stationery. We have designed many greeting card ranges and regularly add new designs to keep our customers coming back for more.

Our handmade greeting cards are refreshingly different and we have built a reputation for a quality, well-produced, innovative product. Our greeting card ranges cover a broad range of styles from modern and contemporary to fun and funky and we cater for every special occasion and sentiment. The response to our greeting cards has been extremely positive and we are proud that our customers include design led shops and department stores such as Fenwicks and Harvey Nichols. If you are interested in becoming one of our stockists then please contact us here: trade enquiry form.

Title: A Perfect Day Wedding Cars
Content:
A Perfect Day Wedding Cars, based in Clayton, Newcastle, Staffordshire, is a family run business with exceptionally high standards. This is reflected in the vehicles which are maintained to the highest level and also in the precise planning and vehicle dress codes which ensure that you will arrive at your wedding relaxed and at the times specified by you. Whilst en-route to the ceremony the chauffeur will put the soft top hood up if requested so that the brides hair remains immaculate for the ceremony. Just prior to the church/venue the hood can be lowered to enable a clear view of your arrival for photographer and family.

We advertise our cars mainly at Wedding Fayres in the North Staffs area. We will be attending more fayres early in 2016 – including Keele Hall on 17th January 2016, Moathouse Stoke on 24th January 2016, Britannia Stadium on 14th February 2016 and Three Horseshoes Inn, Leek on 21st February 2016 – WATCH THIS SPACE. We can show you the cars in all their glory – dressed for the occasion. You can sit in the vehicles, assess their suitability for your wedding, and ask any questions you wish. Alternatively you can call us for a personal viewing at a time to suit you.

Our cars are not restricted to the Stoke on Trent/North Staffordshire area as during the last few seasons we have had commitments in Nottingham, Shropshire and North Wales. We pride ourselves in providing an excellent service for what is your most special of days – A Perfect Day. Our Beaufords have had new Navy Blue hoods fitted to enable them to look pristine for the all seasons.

Title: Brunel's Old Station
Content: This Bristol conference venue offers an outstanding Grade 1 listed Victorian building and is one of the largest events venues in the South West. As one of the oldest train stations in the world, Brunel's original adjoining Passenger Shed is now an atmospheric conference venue which is perfect for an endless variety of events.

Title: Sitting Pretty Affordable Venue Dresses
Content:
Sitting Pretty Weddings have been established since 1997.

We pride ourselves on providing a service which is second to none and work with you to achieve the best possible results for your special day.

We don’t advertise as most of our business comes from recommendations from past clients, hotels and venues.

We’re very proud of our reputation and delighted to feature our customer’s comments on our website. Take a look on our Testimonials page to see what they had to say.

Over the years we have built great relationships with local hotels and wedding venues, our understanding of each venue and knowledge of the rooms, allows us to create the most beautiful rooms, taking advantage of the unique features each venue has to offer.

Title: Beautiful Wishes
Content:
Here at Beautiful Wishes, we are an online supplier of bespoke wedding stationery for your big day. We would be honoured to be there to be a part of your wedding.

We provide bespoke products at affordable prices, and have a full range of wedding stationery, meaning you can relax reassured that your day will be perfect.

All our styles come with a full range of stationery, meaning you can order all your wedding stationery from one place and have a lovely matched themed wedding.

We have all the stationery you need - giving you a full service by offering wedding invitations, evening invitations, save the date cards, RSVP cards, place cards, table plans, engagement, menus, order of service and thank you cards. Plus if you're after a range of stationery, choose from our packages.

With a range of packages to choose from, you can pick the one that's perfect to compliment your big day. Each of our wedding stationery packages also comes with a nice discount from regular pricing - meaning better value for your special day.

Have a browse of our designs to plan your wedding with Beautiful Wishes. We can help you to plan out your big day to get the right style, right mood and right wedding stationery for your perfect day. Sit back, relax and order beautiful designs of wedding stationery online without even leaving the comfort of home.

If you have any queries or questions, please feel free to get in touch with us at info@beautifulwishes.co.uk. We look forward to working with you to make your special day as beautiful as possible!

Title: The Laverton
Content: The Laverton is a 19th-century Italianate gothic palazzo designed by W.J. Stent in 1873 and built for the community of Westbury by Abraham Laverton. This community venue sits conveniently in the heart of Westbury town, just 5 minutes from the High Street. The Laverton venue offers a tailored service according to the clients budget. We have everything you need from a venue, whether it's an elegant room with ample flexible space, a lavish and elegant hall for a wedding reception, a conference room that fits 125 delegates or an easy access venue to Westbury town centre. This period venue is well equipped with a modern kitchen, a piano, full range of audio and technical services, hearing loop, licensed bar, conference facilities, disabled access and unlimited free Wi-Fi. Mid- week weddings and winter weddings can currently be booked for any Monday to Thursday date.

Title: Bath Spa String Quartet
Content:
Welcome to the web site of the Bath Spa String Quartet. A look through our site will give you plenty of information about the services that we can perform. If you do have any questions or comments please contact us and we will respond as soon as we can.string quartet

Bath Spa String Quartet can provide musicians for weddings, civil partnerships, concerts, corporate functions, military dinners, charity fundraising events, funerals, film work, educational music workshops and session work. In fact, as well as having experience in all of the above, we are available for just about any other event that requires live music!

Bath Spa String Quartet was established in 1998 and due to the popularity and success of the original group, we are now able to provide more than one quartet in a day. Our musicians reside in and around the Bath & Bristol area and offer a professional service which is competitively priced. As well as the String Quartet we also offer the option of the Bath Spa String Trio, Solo Violin or Solo Cello to suit all your budget and space requirements. Our repertoire list is extensive, ranging from the standard classical and romantic string quartets through to Swing, Jazz, Ragtime, Show Tunes, TV Themes and arrangements of modern Pop Songs. For a unique touch, we can even arrange your special requests. A full list of the pieces we can perform can be downloaded from our Repertoire page.

We can travel within a one hundred mile radius of Bath and we regularly work in Bath, Bristol, Avon, Somerset, Wiltshire, Gloucestershire, Oxfordshire, Hampshire, Dorset, Devon and Cornwall. Our past performances have included wedding ceremonies, receptions, after dinner dancing, anniversary parties and ceremonial military dinners at venues in and around the Bath area, from the prestigious Royal Crescent Hotel and Castle Combe Manor House to St Audries Park in Bridgwater and Tortworth Court in Gloucestershire.

Title: Elegant Affair Venue Dressing & Chair Covers
Content:
We take great pride in creating photo's that capture the day in full - using professional equipment and a creative eye our imagery will leave you with memories that last a life time.

You will always get TWO photographers, this is incredibly important to us and should be taken into consideration when searching for the right photographer(s). In having a team of two on your day it allows us to

1) Take photos of the Bride and Groom prior to the ceremony

2) Have photos taken within the ceremony from front and behind

3) Circling the day entirely - when one photographer is inside the other is outside. We are never in the same spot at once which can only ensure a full range of memories captured

4) Helps organise guests into the group shots more effectively.

Title: Court Farm

Title: Picture Portraits Ltd
Content:
We are an established business based within the event photography community, specialising within both the Equestrian and Cheerleading communities, although we do regularly cover other sporting event such as football, rugby, motor racing and most other sporting events/sports days.

As active members of SISEP (Society of International School and Event Photographers) we always conduct our services in the professional manner that you would expect of such a company.

Covering most indoor/outdoor events, we strive for perfection and with our don't like don't pay policy you may have your photograph(s) taken without the need or pressure to purchase the image.

We utilise the latest mobile dye sublimation printers for some of the best quality prints available on the market. these will be set up in either our converted event photography bus, one or more of our specially manufactured marquees, or any indoor area of your choosing.

Title: Perfect Planners
Content:
Meet Vicky, Owner Of Perfect Planners

Vicky Nicholas is the owner and lead planner of Perfect Planners. Vicky is a certified wedding planner and destination wedding planner through the Wedding Planners Institute of Canada. Vicky has over 20 years of operational experience in some luxury hotels with planning weddings and corporate events in Canada and the UK.

Vicky has taken the time to work on creating amazing relationships with wedding vendors within the GTA who value customer service and a high standard of product for her clients.

"My passion is to ensure that every wedding is exactly how the couple envisioned their special day to be. We are focused on giving couples an unforgettable and stress-free experience in planning and on their wedding day by creating new and lasting memories."

Title: Shortwood Lodge Golf Club
Content: Shortwood Lodge has been transformed over the last few years and is now one of the most popular golf courses in the area. The undulating parkland golf course extends over 18 holes that are sure to test golfers at any level, and the surrounding countryside provides some spectacular views. The recently refurbished clubhouse will offer a warm welcome to members and visitors alike. With a well-stocked bar, flat screen TV, air conditioning and a pro shop offering a top quality golfing brands at competitive prices, the clubhouse is the ideal place to relax after a round of golf. With two impressive and modern function rooms, Shortwood Lodge also caters for private events. Our Events Coordinator will help to tailor your special occasion to suit your needs, making Shortwood Lodge the ideal place to hold your wedding, birthday or anniversary celebration.

Title: Orchardleigh House
Content: Orchardleigh is a gated and privately owned country estate located in the heart of stunning Somerset, 10 miles from the historic city of Bath. Nestled amidst 500 acres of parkland and lakes, Orchardleigh Estate offers two exclusive use wedding venues, Orchardleigh House and The Walled Garden, as well as two estate Churches, an 18 hole golf course and plenty of luxurious accommodation.

I would love to be involved in your wedding if it is within the Bristol & Bath region.

Title: Queensberry Hotel
Content: Set in a Georgian townhouse, this modern family-run boutique hotel is 10 minutes' walk from Bath Abbey and the Roman Baths, and 12 minutes' walk from the Thermae Bath Spa. Simple, contemporary rooms are individually furnished and have bathrooms with designer toiletries, and feature iPod docks, digital radios and TVs. Upgraded rooms add fireplaces and separate seating areas. Guests receive a complimentary loan of spa packs (towels, robes) for visiting Thermae Bath Spa. There's also free WiFi in public areas. Amenities include a stylish British restaurant, a laid-back elegant cocktail bar, and a drawing room where teas and coffees are served.

Title: The Boathouse
Content: Set in 11 acres of beautiful parkland on the banks of the enchanting Ormesby Broad, The Boathouse is a spectacular country fayre pub and wedding venue. The complete refurbishment of the old Eels Foot pub and boathouse combines one of the most idyllic and romantic wedding venues you will find with fine country dining, luxurious accommodation as well as fully equipped luxury woodland lodges.

Title: Party On
Content:
My name is Bernadette. I have a strong background in customer services having worked in retail for 15 years. I enjoy working with people and have excellent communications skills and I have decided that organising weddings and partys is what I was ment to do and enjoy every minute of it.

I have trained and and have qualified with QC School Of Event Planning Professional (IEWPP Certified). I was so passionate in my studies that the school gave me the highest compliment and awarded me with a AWARD OF MERIT at the end of my studies.

I look forward to working with you to make your wedding or event extra special.

Title: Hilton Bath City Hotel
Content: Overlooking the River Avon, this contemporary hotel is a 5-minute walk from The Roman Baths museum and Bath Abbey. Flat-screen TVs, WiFi (fee), and tea and coffee-making facilities are offered in each modern room; some have rivers views and sofa beds. Suites add separate living areas and minibars. There's a French-style bistro with scenic views, a sophisticated 24-hour lounge and a fitness centre. Other amenities include free WiFi in public spaces and 3 meeting rooms.

Title: Neil Terry Photography
Content:
Established in May 2014, I am an up and experienced photographer based in Bradford, West Yorkshire, UK. I got into photography as an extension to my artwork and discovered that it was something that I really enjoyed, and the feedback I was getting told me that I had a good skill for it. Photography has long been a passion of mine where I used it as an extension to my artwork.

Since I became established as a photographer, my skills and knowledge have increased by a huge amount to the point where my work has been published through various social media websites and in a national newspaper.

My work covers a wide range of subjects including weddings, landscape, weather, political demonstrations, strikes, portraits, abandoned/derelict buildings and nightclub photography.

My website is regularly updated with the best of my images but you can see more on my Facebook page by clicking on the link at the top right of this page.

Title: Coombe Lodge
Content:
Coombe Lodge is now in the caring hands of the PM Hospitality Team, whose reputation has been built on many years of success at Priston Mill. Andrew Carveth had the vision and expertise to implement the changes necessary for moving Coombe Lodge forward by bringing a contemporary feel to the mansion, while retaining its sense of history and grandeur.

From the first call you make to us, to the final hug goodbye as you leave, our wedding organisers are devoted to ensuring your day is exactly what you want. You’ll meet our experienced staff Tom Baxter, Martha Richards, Rebecca Young, Clara Armstrong and Jasmine Motteram, who are responsible for the smooth running of the conferences, weddings and parties.

Dave Bonner the Head Chef, first worked at our sister venue, Priston Mill in 2000. He is committed to delivering a consistently high standard of cuisine at Coombe Lodge (see profile below). He is ably assisted by chefs Ryan Blackman, Jonathan Dyer and Tammy Mitchell.

Leanne Lukins is responsible for much of the administration required for the conferences, accommodation, weddings and party bookings. Head gardener for the extensive gardens, John Bawden, is invaluable in many ways and has the bonus of an amazing and fascinating wealth of knowledge about the history of Coombe Lodge and the local area. He is ably assisted by Josh Bawden and David Jury. Coombe Lodge relies on many others who work behind the scenes, Celia Cameron-Smith, Cathy Bendall, Christine Hearse, Julie Filer, Mel Moore and Maggie Harcourt and an excellent waiting team.

For all of us the aim is to build on our experience, expertise and enthusiasm to make your event ‘captivating, idyllic and altogether enchanting’ and ensure Coombe Lodge is the most wonderful place to get married in Somerset.

Title: Purple Moon Creative Photography
Content:
Jamie & Adam would like to Welcome You to..
Purple Moon...
The Next Generation of Modern Photography with e-Motion.

We are Two Passionate Photographers from Yorkshire with ten years of experience between us, combining this with our exquisite attention to detail we make every couples special memories into truly elegant "Mooving Pictures." With two lenses we are able to capture every Emotion & Motion, using a unique next generation method of dual shots to create what we call at Purple Moon... e-Motion.

We Feel that sense of accomplishment when we piece together all the e-Motions from Your Wedding Day, like the last jigsaw piece falling into place perfectly, creating a timeless memory...

Purple Moon creates something more than "Standard Photography". We marry music with "Mooving Pictures" so that those memories which can easily be forgotten are Brought to Life, allowing us to walk You visually down memory lane... time after time.

We pride ourselves on our creative ability to re-invent traditional wedding photography into a visual magical experience, capturing Your timeless memories in effortless motion. (Inspired by The Harry Potter movies, elegantly showcased)

We understand that Your wedding is unique to You and that it is our duty to unite You and Your partners vision, capturing Your personalities for us to produce eternal memories. We creatively edit and digitally re-master Your photographs as we are able to enhance the e-Motion in each moment and reveal every breathtaking movement through our "Mooving pictures". Elegantly tailoring every Emotion with Motion and Music to create spell binding visuals, which is why our digital albums are so unique and special. When You look back on your photographs we want You to feel and see every emotion unfold and be instantly transported back to Your Wedding Day.

Your Wedding is special to You and it deserves the timeless treatment from Purple Moon, because where it matters to You it matters to us and only "Once in a Purple Moon" do Your photos come alive.


Thank You for Visiting PurpleMoon.info
We hope You enjoyed our Sample Video. If you have any questions please contact us.
(Our new website is coming soon, It's having a Purple Moon makeover..!)

Title: PixiFoto - Family Photography Studios
Content:
Established in 1971, PixiFoto has over 120 in-store professional photography studios. PixiFoto takes pride in being the leading professional permanent and mobile photography studios located across the UK and Ireland.

We pride ourselves in providing our customers with a vibrant, fun & exciting style of contemporary family photography as well as offering more relaxed, traditional style portraits whilst always maintaining great quality & affordability.

So when it comes to beautiful, fun and inspiring portraits of family, friends and all your loved ones, whether it’s the largest family or smallest newborn, the sweetest couple or the cheekiest child, PixiFoto have the expertise and experience to get the best results.

Professional photography isn’t just about taking a picture, it’s about capturing a moment. So why trust anyone else in capturing those magical moments in time, forever!

Our PixiFoto permanent studios are located nationwide in selected Mothercare & Debenhams stores, whilst our PixiFoto pop-up studios visit hundreds of different store locations up and down the country. These include a portfolio of renowned retailers such as Boots, Mothercare, M&Co, Matalan, Superdrug, Asda, Sainsburys, Morrisons, Debenhams, Toys R Us and the Co-op as well as many independent stores. So wherever you are in the UK, there will be a PixiFoto baby, child and family portrait photography studio near you!

Title: Flash Shots Photography
Content:
My name is Nasir Ashraf and I am a freelance photographer offering beautiful and natural images. I provide photography services for all occasions including weddings and parties. I am based in Yorkshire but also cover other counties within the UK.

I became a wedding photographer simply because I love it and I am passionate about providing high quality images that capture all the fun and romance of your day, yet at a competitive cost. I offer a modern and a relaxed style of photography, with a core focus of raw emotion and happiness.

Through my imagination and creativity, I will capture your special day in a traditional and contemporary style. Attention to detail is important, as is blending into the crowd to capture those unposed, natural moments.

Title: Guzelian Ltd
Content:
Yorkshire-based Guzelian has been supplying editorial photography to quality-minded customers – from businesses, to newspapers, to big banks – since 1986.

It’s photography that breathes life into a page – whether it’s in a national newspaper, magazine, corporate brochure or website.

And now these stunning pictures are complemented by news and feature stories produced by our in-house journalists.

We also hold a database of ‘real life’ images built up over 28 years in the business.

And Guzette, our own daily paper (online and in print), is where we preview picture stories for our media clients.

All delivered to the world and your desktop via file transfer, email and direct download.

Title: Alamode Photographers Ltd
Content:
Company Profile

Studio Alamode is a small but successful photography company based in Bradford, West Yorkshire that specialize in the fine art of family, maternity, baby, and childhood portraiture.

Your Photographic Artist

Richard Walker is a full-time, professional photographic artist with over 20 years experience. His photographs have been published internationally and have appeared in numerous magazines as well as on television for the BBC, YTV and Channel 5

Your Assurance of Quality

As well as having a BA (hons) in Editorial Photography Richard has also been awarded the distinction of Associateship by the internationally recognized British Institute of Professional Photography

Title: RJP Wedding Photography
Content:
Choosing the right photographer is one of the most important decisions you have to make when planning your wedding; why? – because when your big day is all over, the lasting memories you will have of it are your wedding photographs.

We can assure you that if you choose us, your wedding will be professionally photographed. We recognise just how important it is for there to be a good relationship between you and your photographer and with that in mind, we will meet with you for an informal chat to discuss your requirements and expectations.

The photos we shoot will tell the story of your wedding, capturing every special moment as it unfolds. Later we shall take those images and create an individually designed album that you can cherish forever. As well as the more traditional and formal shots, we shall unobtrusively mingle with you and your guests taking those unrehearsed magical moments. It is true that the best photographs are of people when they are happy, relaxed and unaware that a camera is pointing at them.

We also produce an Audio Visual Presentation on DVD which is included in three of our packages. We take your wedding images and set them to your choice of music, giving you an additional and easy way to view your photographs.

We take a pride in our work and we promise you our full attention at all times. We take care, but we don’t take over. We shall merely capture the joy of your wedding with no interruption to your day.

We are based in Pembrokeshire although we also cover all of West Wales including Carmarthenshire and Ceredigion and with our prices starting as little as £499, we are certain you will find a package to suit your individual needs. Still not sure, then why not come and see our work for yourselves. Just give us a call – it’s that easy.

Title: Cwm Deri Vineyard
Content:
Cwm Deri Estate is a working smallholding, which first opened to the public in 1992 and the vineyard is now one of Wales' foremost visitor attractions. Visit for a few hours or why not stay with us for a bit longer on our CL site or Static Caravan ?

 

For the very best of Welsh produce, whether it's wine, liqueurs, alcohol-free wines, preserves, cheese, cakes or ice cream, Cwm Deri has something to appeal to all the family, whatever their age.

Enjoy a tasting of our wines and liqueurs, either in our shop or on our patio and terrace, with a commanding view over the vineyard, animals and beyond to the National Park. If you enjoy superb freshly prepared and home-cooked food then you must try our stunning conservatory restaurant.

Relax with your drink and take a leisurely lunch or afternoon tea, secure in the knowledge that Cwm Deri's younger guests will be happily occupied in Pets' Corner. Free Wifi is available!

Title: Mark Little Photography
Content:
Mark Little
​Photographer

Hi my name is Mark Little and I am a Birmingham photographer that specializes in Wedding and Event photography, which gives me a great base to cover this wonderful Country of ours. Distance is no boundary.

I am a qualified member of the Society Of Wedding & Portrait Photography and the Society Of International School and Event Photography Association and together I have been trusted with clients wedding and event photography for over 10 years.

I am blessed to have a wonderful family and the most amazing career. I treasure the images I take of my partner and kids. I love to capture images for clients knowing that, like our own family images, they will treasure them for years to come.

I don’t consider my photography as a job. I have what I call a photographic lifestyle. I love to photograph. Whether for my clients, my partner and kids, my wider family or just for me, I love to capture images. Combine that with my love of peoples stories and you get why I am a wedding and Event photographer.

Spend some time here on my website and get a sense of my varied style. I hope you will see and feel how passionate I am and how I love what I do.

My wholehearted commitment to my clients is to provide top quality, outstanding photography with a level of personal, friendly and trusted service that is second to none.

But I invite you to get in touch and lets have a chat about your hopes, dreams and wishes for your photography.

Title: Pop Dog Photography
Content:
Stuart started his career in photography after graduating his photography course with BA (Hons) in 2001, He learnt his trade and gained vast experience working on commercial and advertising photo shoots for large companies to wedding and portraiture for individuals, working as far afield as America.

Wanting to focus on something different and create someting new, Stuart took his passion for photography and his inspiration from his English Springer Spaniel called Poppins (who had become his muse) and started Pop Dog Photography.

My aim is simple, explore, learn and create the best portraits I can of our loyal friends and celebrate their time with us, whether that be in a colourful, fun pop art style, through a beautiful contemporary fine art portrait or running around their favourite park.

Title: Redhall Estate
Content:
Redhall dates from the 16C and is a country house set in its own traditional parkland close to, yet hidden from the A2 Causeway Coastal Route. It is easily accessible from Belfast International Airport (27m) and George Best City Airport (20m), the port of Larne and from Carrickfergus. The entrance is from the A2 Carrickfergus to Larne road, half a mile on the Larne side of the Ballycarry - Islandmagee crossroads. If using sat nav use postcode BT38 9JN

It has beautiful views over Islandmagee and the ASSI of Larne Lough. The house is privately owned and is in use as a family home.

Title: Photo Digital Art
Content:
Peter Allen is from Stirchley in Birmingham where he’s lived for the past 30+ years. He initially developed the Photo Digital Art style to show off this great city in its best light, but soon realised that it can can applied to almost any situation to make it look better than it does in ‘real life’.

This style is, essentially, the opposite of Photorealism. Start with the PHOTO, apply DIGITAL manipulations to produce painting-like ART. The aim is to make places/objects/buildings look better than they do in normal life, enhanced by the use of vibrant colours and other effects, to make the main subject stand out from its surroundings. A splash of colour to liven up a humdrum world!

Title: Ashley Carr Photography
Content:
After training in Fine Art Ashley became a painter. He formed a cooperative with a group of artists based in Birmingham and went on to create the Works Gallery, a not-for-profit platform that provided graduate art students with exhibition space and support for continuing their work. After a few years exhibiting and as a visiting lecturer Ashley left fine art to become a production manager in a large media firm.

After a company buy out Ashley left media to embark on his photographic career and has never looked back. Working with clients including Virgin Atlantic, Virgin Media, Motorola, Nestlé and Proctor & Gamble Ashley has developed a broad range of skills within the field of photography.

A love of architecture and interior design photography has led Ashley to gain many commissions in this area and his quality Virtual Tour photography has been used by Nandos, Subway, KFC, Knight Frank and the Virgin group.

Title: RoyDavies.com
Content:
Over the coming months I shall be adding new galleries that will show my own personal style of photography and also links to other photographers whose work I enjoy.

In January 2011 I was granted the distinction of Licentiate of The Royal Photographic Society. The process involves presenting a portfolio of work to a panel of judges, on this occasion at the RPS HQ in Bath . It was both a nerve wracking and rewarding experience. The highlight was being asked at the end if the RPS could retain my work for use at future advisory days. It turned out to be a very worthwhile trip!

I hope you enjoy what you see and to those of you that may be considering applying for a RPS distinction – give it a go, you’ll find that it is a most fulfilling and rewarding experience.
