Title: Aaron Scott Richards Photography
Content:
I’m Aaron Scott Richards, Birmingham Event Photographer and part time head shot and travel photographer (That’s me in the picture above trying to look all dark & mysterious like i'm about to embark on an adventure in a J.R.R. Tolkien novel)

If you’ve found me by chance or recommendation looking for an Event Photographer who can capture, create and enhance the essence of your event from awe inspiring speeches, infectious laughter and camaraderie between friends and associates alike then you’ve come to the right place. I don’t JUST photograph events, I seek out and capture expression in people and places as they unfold naturally using an experienced and cultivated know-how that I’ve developed & learned through working in the creative industry for over 10 years.

Whether your an Event professional or family member on the hunt for a Birmingham based Event Photographer to cover your event, you can fire up the kettle, call off the dogs, cancel the search party and rest easy.

After a quick phone call telling me a bit about your Event, the rest is effortless. I can work too extensive briefs, but I’m just as at home following my nose seeking out those moments that make headlines, not just in news papers, but in hearts & minds too.

Capturing eye-catching, beautifully cool photos is what I do, so you can share and create a real buzz around your event with the world long after the event has concluded. If like me, you like to see a little proof in the pudding or photos as it would be in this case, then why not take a look at some of the Event Photography I have covered in Birmingham on my home page http://www.aaronscottrichards.co.uk/ then finish up with a quick read of some of my clients testimonials http://www.aaronscottrichards.co.uk/testimonials/

Title: Lagan Valley Island s
Content:
About
Historic Lagan Valley Island siteSituated on an island in the heart of Lisburn city, Lagan Valley Island is one of Northern Ireland's premier venues.

The site on which Lagan Valley Island was built once played a significant role in Lisburn's industrial past. Previously the site for the Island Mill Spinning Company, famous for the production on linen through it, production at the Mill came to an end in 1983. When this happened, Lisburn City Council (then Lisburn Borough Council) purchased the site and with funding assistance from the National Lottery to the Arts Council of Northern Ireland, regeneration of this site began.

The building opened for business in March 2001 and was officially opened in November 2001 by Her Majesty the Queen. Lagan Valley Island has many functions; It is headquarters of Lisburn & Castlereagh City Council and the facility is also a unique mix of civic, business and arts facilities - home to council offices, the Island Arts Centre, Council Chambers, a purpose built Conference Centre, Theatre, and stunning wedding facilities

Content: Stacey is a fully qualified and highly experienced makeup artist. Although based at her purpose-built studio in Co. Title: Orchid Studio
Content:
AttOrchid Bridal Studio we have over 10years experience in the Bridal Industry and pride ourselves in being The One Stop Bridal Shop. Offering a selection of Designer Gowns by Justin Alexnader, Sincerity, Enzoni, Eternity and Bellice. The new 2015/16 gowns are now in store including our fabulous Bridesmaids collections by designers Kelsey Rose and Veromia.

After you have chosen your dream dress and beautiful bridesmaids gowns its time to choose your Wedding Flowers -- Wedding Cake -- Venue Styling including Chair Covers -- Backdrop -- Candy Cart and many other accessories to keep your guests in awe the whole day through. We will also help you choose a theme for your special day and have this running from beginning to end so your Wedding Day is everything you could have wished for.

Our award winning florist can work with the simple elegant look to the more flamboyant, from churches and chapels to registry offices or civil ceremonies. The flowers can then be transfered to the reception and used to decorate the function room at your choosen venue.

When it comes to your Wedding Cake our award winning designer will create a cake to compliment your chosen theme or if you prefer something totally different then he will design one to your liking with flavours to tempt every pallet.

We have recently opened a Sale Room with ex-sample dresses at much reduced prices.

Orchid Bridal Studio operate by appointment only, so please call us to arrange this in advance on 028 38 392121

Orchid Studio 115-117 Bridge Street, Portadown, Co Armagh, BT63 5AA
